title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix butter and dressing mix; spread 1/2 in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Precook zucchini and onion in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain and spread over crumbs in pan.
Mix together sour cream, soup and grated carrot.
Pour over crumb mixture in pan.
Cover with the remaining 1/2 of crumb mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: fred's baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients (can add some juice from the beans) and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: hellmann's hawaiian carrot cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Stir together flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
In large bowl, beat eggs, sugar, mayonnaise and pineapple until well blended.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in carrots and walnuts. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: grape conserve
directions: Add to grapes and sugar.
Cook approximately 20 minutes.

title: mexican salsa
directions: In medium-large saucepan, combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Ladle into hot canning jars, securing lids with jar rings.
Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes or store in covered container in refrigerator.
Makes 2 pints.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Brown beef in skillet; add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except spaghetti.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Add to broccoli mixture slowly until thickened.
Put several spoons of broccoli mixture in white mixture before adding to the broccoli mixture.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in medium bowl; mix well.
Combine eggs, milk and vanilla; stir into dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until pie is set.
Cool on wire rack.
Lightly sift powdered sugar over pie.

title: eggs n more
directions: Mix eggs and milk in bowl.
Scramble.
Bake potatoes; remove skin.
Chop potatoes and add to eggs.
Add onions, salt and pepper.
Cook together until all is warm.

title: 30 minute apple butter
directions: Cook and stir together for 20 minutes.
Add 1 cup red cinnamon candy and 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon.
Cook and stir 10 minutes longer.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, chill and enjoy.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Dump pineapple and pie filling, swirling around and filling all corners. Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit to cover it all. Melt butter and dribble over top. Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix milk and yeast together.
Add oil and salt.
Gradually add flour, kneading final 2 cups in by hand.
Let dough raise until it doubles in size.
Spread out on pizza pans.
Bake at 425° for approximately 15 minutes.
Top with favorite toppings and bake until cheese on top is brown.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Combine apricot preserves, onion soup mix and Russian dressing together.
Spread mixture on chicken.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: date muffins
directions: Prepare the mixture at least 24 hours before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy cheesy beef enchiladas(20 minutes to make)
directions: Brown the beef in a large skillet. Drain the meat. Mix in the taco seasoning. Add the water and simmer over low heat. Place 3 to 4 tablespoons of meat in each flour tortilla. Roll and place seam down in a glass pan. Continue until all meat is gone and pan is full. Then top with salsa con queso and cheese. Microwave 6 to 8 minutes. Serve with hot sauce, chips, beans and fresh tomatoes, if they like 'em. Serves 6 to 8.

title: k f c buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine all of the ingredients.
Knead the dough by hand until smooth.
Flour your hands.
Pat the dough flat to 3/4-inch thickness on waxed paper and cut out biscuits with a biscuit cutter. Bake on a greased baking sheet for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine egg, milk and salt together.
Then add all-purpose flour to the mixture until a stiff dough forms.
Roll very thin on a floured surface.
Set aside 20 minutes.
Slice 1/4-inch wide. Spread out and let dry for 2 hours.
Drop into boiling broth and cook, uncovered, until tender.

title: peanut butter chip chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake, cookies will be soft.
They will puff during baking, flatten upon cooling.
Cool on cookie sheet until set.
Remove to wire rack and cool completely.

title: greek hot dog sauce
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add spices and rest of ingredients.
Cook slowly, stirring often, until thickened.
Serve over hot dogs and hamburgers.
This recipe freezes well.

title: barbecue kraut
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain well.	Combine sauerkraut, tomato sauce, brown sugar and hamburger and onion mixture.	Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine, and eggs.
Mix together flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, and salt.
Add both together and mix well.
Add cherries, raisins, and pecans.
Line 2 loaf pans with foil.
Add batter and bake at 275° for 2-1/4 hours.
When cool, wrap in cloth dampened with orange juice for 1 week.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Knead dough only enough to hold together.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pasta fresca
directions: In medium bowl mix eggs, flour and salt.
Knead 2 to 3 minutes.
Add small amounts of flour until dough is no longer sticky.
Roll dough through pasta machine and cut as desired.

title: peach tart
directions: Mix flour, 1/4 cup of sugar and salt.
Cut in 1 stick of butter until very fine.
Press on bottom and sides of a 9-inch deep pie plate.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together.
Spoon into crust and refrigerate.
Serve with cherry topping, if desired.

title: strawberry mold
directions: You will need a 12 x 8 x 2-inch relish dish.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix flour, eggs, salt, mustard and sugar.
Heat vinegar and water, not boiling, just warm.
Add the egg mixture and cook until it thickens.
Stir constantly so it won't scorch.
This will keep in refrigerator for weeks.
Great for potato salad!

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until done and drain off water.
Add half and half and beat or mash until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Put mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Cover and refrigerate.
(Will keep for a week.)
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 14.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) layer cake pans; line bottoms with wax paper. Mix cocoa, 1/3 cup sugar and milk in medium-size saucepan. Heat over low heat until bubbles appear around edge of pan, stirring constantly.

Cool to room temperature. Sift flour, 1 cup sugar, soda and salt into large bowl of mixer. Add shortening, eggs, cocoa mixture and vanilla. Beat on low speed just until ingredients are moistened, scraping bowl frequently. Beat on medium speed 3 minutes. Pour into pans. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pans. Remove wax paper.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Cream the shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in sweet potatoes and water.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves. Add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Fold in pecans and raisins.
Spoon into 2 well-greased and floured
9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until bread tests done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken garden pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, parsley, basil and garlic.
Add Cheddar cheese, broccoli and noodles.
Gently mix in tomato and black olives.
Just before serving, sprinkle with cashew halves.

title: crispy potato chicken
directions: Peel and grate potatoes; put into water for 5 minutes.
Drain and pat dry.
Mix in olive oil.
Put chicken, bone side down, in a foil-lined pan.
Spread each with mustard mix (mustard and garlic).
Form a skin over each breast with potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and cilantro. Bake at 425°, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pasta lite
directions: Boil pasta per package directions.
In a small pan saute the remaining ingredients.
When the pasta is done, rinse well with hot water.
Pour sauteed mixture over pasta and toss until well mixed.
Sprinkle lightly with favorite pasta cheese after serving. Has approximately 260 calories per serving.

title: crispy candy nest
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add next 2 and mix well. Drop by 1/3 cupful onto greased
cookie
sheet.
Shape into next by pushing with greased thumb.
Dust bottom of nest with powdered sugar. Fill with peanut M&M's to look like eggs.
Makes 10 to 12 nests.

title: adobo
directions: Cut meat into chunks about the size of walnuts.

title: tiny pizzas
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Mix.
Add cheese; mix thoroughly.
Spread about 1 teaspoon of mixture on each cracker; top with a thin slice of link sausage.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 5 to 6 minutes.
Yields about 50 pizza rounds.

title: hidden valley ranch chicken breasts
directions: Whisk juice and dressing mix together.
Marinate breasts for 24 hours in half the juice mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Combine cornstarch, water and remaining juice mixture in saucepan.
Heat to thicken.
Serve sauce with chicken.

title: apricot orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water add the balance of the first 4 items, and partially set in a 9 inch square pan.
Cook orange juice, sugar, flour and egg until thickened.
Cool Add whipped cream. Spread over first layer.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese on top.

title: pea salad
directions: Spread peas over first 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle garlic salt (very little) over top of peas.
Spread mayonnaise over top of peas until completely covered.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top of mayonnaise.
Slice olives thin and put on top of cheese.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ham, pork and hamburger into saucepan with water and with eggs, crackers crumbs and milk.
Shape into loaf.
Mix sugar, water and vinegar together.
Spoon on top of loaf before and during baking.
Bake until done.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix well and spread into greased baking pan.
Sprinkle top with garlic salt.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: turtle cake
directions: Beat until
smooth and spread on cool cake.
Put nuts on cake if desired.

title: scotch bread
directions: Knead well, put into 11 x 17 pan. Prick all way through with fork. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Cut while hot and leave in pan until cool.

title: quick corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder and mix together.
Add milk, oil and eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Pour batter 1/2 inch deep into greased cake pans.
The shallow amount of batter will yield a thin and crisp corn bread.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes or until batter is firm to the touch and lightly browned.
Cut into squares and serve at once with margarine, honey or jams.

title: fish fillet roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add lemon juice, bouillon and Tabasco sauce.
Heat slowly.
Set aside. In medium bowl, combine cooked rice, spinach, cheese and 1/4 cup lemon-butter sauce.
Mix well.
Divide rice and spinach mixture equally among fillets.
Roll up and place seam-side down in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over roll-ups.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake 25 minutes or until fish flakes.

title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package.
Put into a bowl and layer, alternating vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture. Top with light Cool Whip.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook in 4-quart pan 3/4 full of water.
Add salt and pepper.
When cooked, do not drain.
Add after cooking the butter, milk and cheese.
Stir constantly until melted.
(A little thickening may be added.)

title: classic crisco flaky 9-inch double pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in medium bowl.
Cut in Crisco using pastry blender (or 2 knives) until all flour is just blended in to form pea-size chunks.
Sprinkle with water, one tablespoon at a time.
Toss lightly with fork until dough forms a ball.
Divide dough into two equal parts.
Press between hands to form two 5 to 6 inch pancakes.
Flour "pancakes" lightly on both sides.
Roll between sheets of waxed paper (or plastic wrap) on dampened countertop.
Peel off top sheet.
Trim one inch larger than upside down 9-inch pie plate.
Flip into pie plate.
Remove other sheet. Trim edge even with pie plate.
Moisten edge of pastry with water. Add your choice of filling.
Roll top crust same as bottom.
Peel off top sheet.
Flip onto filled pie.
Remove other sheet.
Trim 1/2 inch beyond edge of pie plate.
Fold top edge under bottom crust.
Flute.
Cut slits in top crust for escape of steam.
Bake according to recipe for pie filling.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: pennie carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients with cooked carrots; chill and serve cold.

title: doubletree post oak christmas cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla. Beat at low speed until mixed. Combine dry ingredients in a separate bowl. Slowly fold flour into the butter mixture. Add lemon juice concentrate; blend well. Fold in white chocolate, cranberries and nuts.

title: beef salami
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and refrigerate for 3 days.
On the third day, take out and knead for 5 minutes, then return to refrigerator.
On the morning of the fourth day, shape into 3 rolls.
Put each roll in separate sheet of foil (shiny side against hamburger).
Prick foil in several places with fork. Place on rack with drip pan under it and bake for 3 to 3 1/2 hours at 200°.

title: bean loaf
directions: Mix beans, chopped spices and bread crumbs or egg.
Form into a well defined loaf.
Use large loaf pan.
Put cheese on top and smooth sauce all over top and sides.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes. Serve hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: Allow sausage and grated cheese to get to room temperature. Mix together with hands all ingredients, adding Bisquick 1 cup at a time.
Form into balls and bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Place above ingredients in blender except for the oil.
Blend short time, then add oil.
Beat 3 to 5 minutes.

title: quick and easy frosting
directions: Beat 1 cup powdered sugar and egg white at high speed for 1 minute.
Stop mixer and add the other cup of powdered sugar and the remaining ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
May add 1/2 cup cocoa for chocolate frosting.
Refrigerates well.

title: rhubarb gelatin salad
directions: Put tomato sauce into a pint jar with a tight fitting lid. Add the salt, dill seed, basil, sugar and oregano.
Add a few grindings of pepper, then add the vinegar, onion and Worcestershire.
Cover and shake well.
Chill.
Shake well again before using.
Makes about 2/3 cup.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Add onion to vegetables; cook halfway, according to directions.
Drain, saving 1 cup liquid.
Add liquid and soup to vegetables.
Melt oleo; add stuffing mix to it.
Put 1/2 of oleo and stuffing in the vegetable mixture.
Put in casserole dish; top with the remaining oleo and stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: reunion salad
directions: Clean, trim and cut up broccoli into small flowerettes. In a large bowl, combine onions, raisins and pecans. Mix together salad dressing, milk, vinegar and Equal, stirring until smooth. Pour dressing over salad. Add salt and pepper to taste. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Top with bacon bits and toss before serving.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put broccoli on bottom. Arrange chicken slices on top.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Mix crumbs with melted margarine or butter.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: fried quail
directions: Combine flour, salt and black and red peppers; mix well and set aside.
Combine
egg
and milk and beat until blended. Dredge quail in flour
mixture,
dip in egg mixture and dredge again in flour
mixture.
In
a
large cast-iron skillet, heat enough oil to cover
quail
and
fry quail until golden brown, turning occasionally.
Drain
on
paper towels.
You will have to fry in two batches so keep first batch warm in 250° oven.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Boil sugar and water; let cool.
Then mix in all of the above ingredients.
Freeze.

title: mexican chalupa
directions: Place roast and beans in deep roaster and cover with water. Add next 7 ingredients.
Cook, covered, at least 8 hours over heat to simmer.
Stir occasionally.
Remove roast bone.
Spoon over crushed Doritos or Tostitos.
Top with:

title: lydia's pizzelles
directions: You need a pizzelle iron to make this cookie.

title: jello pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar and pineapple juice.
Cook slowly for 2 minutes, then add jello.
Whip the cream and add to other ingredients.
Put in a graham cracker pie shell or a vanilla wafer crust.
Chill several hours.

title: tomato salsa
directions: Use a non-metallic bowl and mix all ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: pork and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Partially freeze pork; slice thinly into bite-size strips. Stir together soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and ginger.
Set aside.

title: tuna salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Dissolve over hot water.
Mix with other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: spinach dip for fresh vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables and fruits.

title: mexican dip
directions: Peel, seed and mash avocados.

Stir in next 4 ingredients. Spread in casserole dish. Spread sour cream over avocado mix. Spoon drained picante over sour cream. Spoon on remaining ingredients (olives, tomatoes and cheese), except beans. Spread beans around the edges of the casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bacon. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except onion rings. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and put onion rings on top. Bake for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Beat eggs and add all other ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into unbaked (9-inch) pie crust.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: haystacks(candy)
directions: Use double boiler to dissolve caramels and peanut butter.
Mix potato shoestrings and peanuts.
Pour first mixture over second mixture.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour in muffin tins.
Bake until brown at 350°.
Makes 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, in large baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam, for 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix the flour, salt and Crisco until crumbly.
Add the milk; do not handle much.
Roll into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes for empty pie shells.

title: rice
directions: Mix all together and bake in casserole dish.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin slices, but do not cut all the way through.
Put potatoes in baking dish.
Fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt; drizzle with butter and sprinkle with herbs. Bake potatoes at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: tuna fish spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken bulgarian
directions: Combine yogurt, salt, garlic, cardamon, chili powder and cinnamon.
Marinate chicken in yogurt mixture at least 4 hours (overnight is best).
Place chicken in baking pan, skin side up. Combine flour with marinade and spoon over chicken.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours or until tender in 350° oven.
Baste occasionally with marinade.
Serves 4.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon; drain, crumble and reserve.
Saute next 4 ingredients until tender in 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Add next 4 ingredients; heat until hot.
Add more milk if the soup seems too thick.
Stir in reserved bacon.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve hot.

title: pancakes!
directions: Combine all ingredients until smooth.
Spray griddle with nonstick spray and set it over moderate heat.
If you want small pancakes, drop about 2 tablespoons of the batter onto the griddle or pour about 1/4 cup for larger pancakes, if desired.
Bake until full of bubbles on the top and the underside is lightly browned. Turn with a spatula and brown other side.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 2 eggs and margarine.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking dish.
Mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)
When top is brown and crispy it will be done.

title: honey mustard ham
directions: Heat grill.
In small bowl, combine honey and mustard; blend well.
When ready to barbecue, place ham slice on gas grill over medium heat or on charcoal grill 4 to 6 inches from medium-high coals.
Brush with half of the honey mixture.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated, turning and brushing once with remaining honey mixture.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple, juice and all, in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spoon on cherry filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over all.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle on walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff peaks can be made.
Add salt and mix in.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Place aluminum foil on cookie sheet.
Drop dough by teaspoon on ungreased foil.
Place cookies in oven.
Close oven door. Immediately turn oven off.
Leave cookies in closed oven overnight.
Peel cookies off foil in the morning.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and bread; add onion soup mix, sage, pepper, salt and poultry seasoning.
Stir in eggs, celery soup, chicken soup and enough broth to make a very moist dressing.
Stuff turkey lightly with dressing.
Place remaining dressing in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan; bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until browned.
Stir once or twice during first 20 minutes of baking.
This dressing freezes well.
Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: kids clay ornaments
directions: Mix water, salt and flour in a bowl with your hands.
This forms the clay.
Take bits of clay and make different shapes. Place each shape on a baking sheet covered with foil.
Make a hole at the top of each shape with a pencil.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour until brown.
Let shapes cool and paint them and glitter them. Coat the shapes with shellac.
String with yarn to hang on your Christmas tree.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: On split muffin, spread with canned pizza sauce. Add salami or pepperoni. Top with grated cheese and place under broiler until cheese is melted and begins to bubble.

title: eggplant appetizer(caponata)
directions: Wash and cube eggplant; sprinkle with salt and let stand. Squeeze dry and saute in oil until soft.
Drain and set aside. Brown onion in oil.
Add tomatoes, olives and celery and cook slowly about 15 minutes.
Return eggplant to pan and add capers. Heat vinegar; add and dissolve sugar in vinegar and then pour over eggplant.
Correct seasoning with salt and pepper.
Cover pan and cook very slowly over a low heat for 20 minutes, stirring to prevent sticking.
Serve hot or cold.
This keeps very well and is excellent in an antipasto served with crackers.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in eggs, salt and pepper (mixed).
Roll in bread crumbs.
Brown in hot oil.
Drain.
Place in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients except cheeses.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put Mozzarella cheese on top and bake until it melts.

title: chicken crescent squares
directions: Blend together cream cheese and 2 tablespoons melted margarine. Add chicken, pepper, milk, onion, optional pimento and a sprinkle of tarragon.
Mix thoroughly.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles, sealing perforations.
Place about 1/2 cup chicken mixture on each rectangle.
Pull four corners of dough to center and seal.
Brush tops with remaining margarine and dip into bread crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: blue ribbon banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend dry ingredients together and add alternately with mashed bananas.
Add flavoring and chopped nuts.
Pour mixture into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch bread pans that have been lightly greased and floured on bottom only.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until a toothpick inserted in center of loaf comes out dry.
Remove from oven and cool bread in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and continue to cool on wire rack.
Place in clean plastic bags or foil.
Allow bread to ripen overnight before slicing.
Flavor develops upon standing.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Set aside.
Heat soup in saucepan. Keep boiling and mix in the cream cheese with beater.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin.
Cool a few minutes and add mayonnaise, shrimp and vegetables.
Mix thoroughly and pour into slightly oiled fish mold.
When set, unmold on serving tray. Place a slice of green olive with pimiento for eye for fish. Serve with assorted crackers.
This is best if made a day ahead of time.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs
until
fluffy.
Add	sugar, vanilla and oil. Mix flour,
baking
soda,
salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture. Blend
well.
Add apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Powdered sugar may be sprinkled on top when cool.

title: carole's all-night salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in order given.
Layer the cheese and sugar in order given.
Chill overnight and toss when you're ready to serve.

title: mashed potato nests
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring constantly, until tender.
Stir in potatoes, then add next 3 ingredients.

title: beer tempura batter
directions: Place eggs, flour and salt in bowl; mix well.
Gradually stir in beer; beat just until smooth.
Let stand 1 hour or refrigerate overnight.
Yields approximately 2 cups.

title: sherry chicken with rice
directions: Rinse chicken breasts with cold water and pat dry.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt oleo.
Add cake mix and 2/3 cup of Pet milk.
Pour half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup of Pet milk; pour over baked cake. Sprinkle chocolate chips over caramels, then the pecans.
Cover this by pouring the rest of the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto well-greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400°.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix all together.
Cook for 30 minutes, stirring constantly. Do not let stick to pan while cooking.
Put in jars.
Seal jars. Place jars in pot of water.
Cover pot.
Let cook about 10 minutes.

title: unbelievable popovers
directions: Combine and stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Ignore lumps and spoon into cold cupcake pan (well greased).
Makes 12 cupcakes.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake for 5 to 10 minutes more.
Delicious served as rolls or with afternoon snack.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown chuck and sausage together.
Drain well.
Set aside. Cube cheese and microwave on High until melted.
Add the meats, soup and Ro-Tel to cheese.
Mix well.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Stir and spread first layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until light brown.

title: spinach pudding
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package, but without adding water. Drain thoroughly.
Mix batter in heavy pan; add flour, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk gradually.
Stir into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in pan of hot water and bake for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.
Serve from casserole or unmold.

title: spinach new orleans
directions: Cook and drain the spinach.
Combine with margarine and cream cheese.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Italian dressing.
Pour Italian dressing over all.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: low-fat pineapple spread
directions: Soften cream cheese; add vanilla pudding (dry). Add pineapple. Stir until well blended.
Especially good on graham crackers or bagels.

title: frozen corn
directions: Combine all; boil lightly for 10 minutes.
Cool, bag and freeze.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and powdered sugar together until smooth.
Roll into balls and place on waxed paper.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and wax together until smooth.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate mixture and place back on wax paper to dry.
Store in cool place.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Very good over chicken.
Covers 6 or 8 breast halves.
Sprinkle with garlic and butter.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°, covered.
Then add barbecue sauce and cook, covered, 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove cover and cook 30 minutes more. Two hours baking time.

title: taco chip dip
directions: Spread jalapeno bean dip in bottom of pan.
Mix 1 cup Hellmann's and 1/2 cup Green Goddess and spread over bean dip.
Mix 1 package taco mix, 1/2 cup Hellmann's and 1 cup sour cream; spread over Green Goddess.
Add 1 large package shredded Cheddar cheese, tomatoes and green onions, etc., then dig in!

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix salt and water.
Soak whole cucumbers in brine water for 14 days.
Wash, slice and soak overnight in alum water.
Rinse and soak overnight in vinegar.
Pour off vinegar.
Add sugar and spice in cloth to cucumbers and let stand.
The sugar will make plenty of syrup to cover the pickles.
The pickles are never heated and sealing is not necessary.
Will be ready in 2 to 3 weeks.
If you want to add cauliflower, break in small pieces and put in brine water with cucumbers.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Combine onion, cheese and corned beef.
Add soup and milk.
Pour in a greased casserole dish.
Top with chips or crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Check oven at 40 minutes for this is a high altitude dish. Great for potlucks.

title: mexican fiesta pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Form sausage into 1-inch balls.
Brown in skillet, cooking until done.
Drain fat.
Add red beans, onion, chili sauce and chili powder.
Heat.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Fix package of corn muffin mix according to instructions on the box.
From into a ring over beans.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: skillet sticky chicken
directions: Fry chicken until brown on all sides; pour off fat.
In small bowl, mix remaining ingredients well.
Stir into skillet.
Reduce heat to low.
Return chicken to skillet; cook for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with chicken.
Put diced onion and green pepper on top of chicken.
Add salt and pepper.
Microwave all liquids (soups, chilies and broth).
Cut cheese on top of chicken.
Crush 1/2 bag of Doritos by hand and layer on top of cheese; pour liquids over top and add rest of crushed Doritos. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: *If using frozen shell, it is good to bake it a little.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin (do not peel).
Add sliced onions and cover with 1/3 cup salt.
Cover with cracked ice and mix.
Soak for 3 hours; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients, then pour over cucumbers.
Heat to boiling.
Put in jars and seal.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix salad dressing as directed.
Drain mushrooms and place in dressing to marinate overnight.
Mushrooms are ready to serve.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Cook onion, celery and butter in a saucepan until tender. Tear bread into pieces in a mixing bowl; add cooked onion and celery, egg and poultry seasoning.
Mix all together with water and set aside.
Flatten chicken breasts with a rolling pin.
Spoon stuff in chicken breast.
Roll up and fasten with a toothpick. Place in a baking dish with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Line
pie
plate
with crushed vanilla wafers. Stand up whole vanilla
wafers
around
edges.
Mix the sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice. Stir in eggs real good.

title: pie crust mix
directions: Cut Crisco into flour and salt.
Keep in Ziploc bag in refrigerator.
Stores well for several weeks.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time. Mix flour, baking powder and soda. Add sour cream. Add flour gradually until blended. Add vanilla and lemon. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Use first five items to make cake.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Ice cake and sprinkle coconut over all.

title: turkey stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees.
In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium-high heat; brown the sausage, stirring to break up, then drain off excess liquid.
Add the cream cheese, salt, pepper, dillweed, and scallions to the sausage; mix.

Stuff the mushrooms with the sausage mixture, place on cookie sheets that have been coated with nonstick vegetable spray, sprinkle with bread crumbs, and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Transfer to a serving platter and serve warm.
YIELD:
about 40 stuffed mushrooms.

title: our favorite apple pie
directions: Line bottom of pie pan with 1/2 pastry.
Mix flour, salt, cinnamon and sugars.
Spread half of this mixture over bottom of pastry.
Pour in can of apples.
Pour the other half of flour and sugar mixture over apples. Dot with butter.
Make crisscross top for the pie, using the remaining 1/2 of pastry.
Brush with cream and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Turn heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Make paste of coloring and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add salt, vanilla and flour alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in vinegar and soda mixture.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured 2 layer cake pans, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chop suey
directions: Bring to boil and simmer one hour or until meat is tender. Add soy sauce (as desired); cook 1/2 hour.
Add one can bean sprouts and bring to a boil. Thicken with cornstarch.
Top with Chinese noodles over rice.

title: pepper glazed chicken
directions: In nonstick skillet cook breasts until almost done.
Add jelly; cook 5 minutes, coating well.

title: samboosa holwah(fried nut triangles)
directions: Combine cashew nuts and walnuts in a bowl with sugar and ground cardamom to taste.
Add water (2 teaspoons) and knead well with hands until mixture clings together in a coarse paste.

title: stuffed spicy clams
directions: Steam clams in water just until they open.
Remove the whole clams from the shells.
Save 1/2 of each shell.
Preheat broiler and place clams back on 1/2 shell.
Combine the remainder of ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Spread 1 teaspoon on each clam and lightly sprinkle with cheese.
Place under broiler 3 to 4 minutes until lightly browned.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Crumble crackers on top.
Melt 1 stick margarine and spoon on top of crackers.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: oatmeal ready-to-go cake
directions: Mix boiling water and oats; set aside to cool.
Blend remaining ingredients well on low speed.
Add oatmeal and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken fried pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Mix egg and milk.
Dip meat on all sides in egg and milk mixture, then in crushed croutons.
Cook meat until brown on both sides.
Season with salt.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Cover; cook in microwave on Braise for 20 minutes.

title: sparkling ale punch
directions: Blend cranberry juice, sugar and fruit juices.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Add sherbet and ginger ale when ready to serve.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet with crescent rolls; bake as directed.
Blend cream cheese, mayo and Hidden Valley mix until smooth; spread on crust when cool.
Arrange cauliflower, broccoli and green peppers; add carrots and cheese and refrigerate.
Cut into squares for serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple evenly in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread pie filling and dry cake mix evenly over pineapple. Sprinkle pecans over cake mix, and slice margarine in pats over top of it all. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Line pan with shells.
Layer with beef, cheese and onion. Pour tomato and enchilada sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a 3-quart casserole (ungreased), mix all of the ingredients together.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 50 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent a hard crust from forming on top.
Add regular milk if it gets too dry.

title: apple cake squares
directions: Beat the sugar, eggs and oil until creamy.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; add to creamed mixture. Fold in the chopped apples.
Bake in a well-greased 9 x 13 1/2-inch pan at 350° for about 40 minutes.
When almost cool, cut into squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: methodist preacher chicken
directions: Melt the
butter.
Dip pieces of chicken in it and then roll the chicken in a mixture made from remaining ingredients. Place in a shallow dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. If the chicken gets too brown, just add a little water.

title: squirrel cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs until light.
Add flour with baking powder sifted in.
Spread on baking sheet, buttered and floured.
Spread thin.
Sprinkle a cup of nuts over this.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and put in flat pan (9 x 13-inch).
Add drained fruit cocktail and bananas and let set.
Heat pineapple and cornstarch until its thick.
Beat Dream Whip and add softened cream cheese.
Mix with cooled pineapple and spread over Jell-O.

title: peas and broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange one package of broccoli (thawed) in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with peas.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, onions, cheese and eggs.
Pour 1/2 sauce over broccoli.
Put next package of broccoli and remaining sauce.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients; add warm water and poppy seed.
Spray loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Can also use Bundt pan.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions.
Add other ingredients. Mix well.
Add enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: french dressing
directions: In screw-top jar, combine salad oil, vinegar, lemon juice, sugar, dry mustard, salt, paprika and pepper.
Cover; shake well. Chill.
Shake well before serving.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and oleo in a pan.
Let come to a boil. Test a teaspoonful at a time in a cup of cold water until it forms a soft ball you can pick up with your fingers.
Remove from heat; add marshmallow, peanut butter, oleo and vanilla.
Mix together by hand and beat until thick enough to pour in a greased pan.
Let cool; cut in pieces.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil whole potatoes until tender.
Take off skin; slice thin. Put in buttered Pyrex dish a layer of potatoes, sprinkled with sugar, cinnamon and butter.
When dish is filled, sprinkle top layer of potatoes with sugar, butter, cinnamon and orange peel. Add water; bake until brown and well candied, about 30 minutes, at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and margarine in large bowl. Add the boiling water and mix.
Sift dry ingredients into this mixture and mix well.
Add the eggs and vanilla and mix.
Pour into a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
So easy and very moist.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Toss all ingredients together and add 2 cups broth.
Mix well. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
If too dry, add more broth.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until crispy on top.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Chop onion and chipped beef.
Mix sour cream, mayo, parsley and dill weed with chopped onion and chipped beef.
Scoop out middle of rye bread and cut into cubes.
Place on a tray around hollow rye bread.
Put filling in the middle of the cut-out loaf of bread. Eat dip with bread.
Serves a party!

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Put starter in refrigerator 3-5 days.
Take out and feed with the following:
3/4 cup sugar, 3 teaspoons instant potatoes, 1 cup Pillsbury bread flour, 1 cup warm water.
Mix well with starter. Let stand out of refrigerator all day (8-12 hours).
This will not rise, just bubble.
Take out 1 cup of starter to use for making bread.
Return remaining starter to refrigerator.
Keep 3-5 days, then feed again.
If you do not make bread, discard or divide with a friend.

title: open face cake
directions: Work softened butter into dry ingredients.
Blend in eggs. Grease flat pan (9-inch square okay).
Press batter in pan and up sides of pan.
Fill with fruit filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: methodist preschool sugar cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar
together.
Beat
in
eggs until fluffy (one at a time).
Add
vanilla,
then
stir
in
4 cups flour. This cookie dough is wonderful for children because it does not stick to their hands.

title: green punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: broiled orange roughy
directions: Rinse fish.
Soak in cold water with 1 tablespoon sea salt. (Sea salt takes the fishy taste away).
Soak until ready to use. Brush olive oil over fillets.
Season with salt, pepper and onion powder to taste.
Drizzle lemon juice over fillets; sprinkle with parsley over all.
Broil until fish begins to turn light brown, or until flakes with a fork.

title: biscotti
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form dough into loaves.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into pieces after baking.
Refrigerate to cool.

title: harvey wallbanger cake(serves 12 to 16)
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan 45 to 50 minutes (350°).
Cool right side up about 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and drizzle frosting over cake.

title: fruity yogurt ice
directions: Place undrained raspberries, peaches, blueberries or apricot halves in a blender container or food processor bowl.
Blend or process until smooth.
If using raspberries, strain them to remove seeds.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together blended fruit, yogurt and honey.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and freeze for 3 to 4 hours or until firm.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring butter, sugar and Karo to a boil, then boil 2 minutes. Put popcorn in brown paper bag; add 1/4 teaspoon baking soda to mix and stir.
Pour over popcorn in bag.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, shaking bag each time.
Stir while cooling, spread on wax paper.

title: paul's stir-fried rice with ground beef
directions: Heat the wok, then add oil.
Put the mixed vegetables in the hot wok.
Stir-fry the mixed vegetables for about 5 minutes.
Add the beef and stir until it's cooked.
Then add the rice, salt, ketchup and sugar.
Stir-fry until the rice is fried.

title: oatmeal squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add soup, sugar, eggs and oil; mix well with a spoon (about 350 strokes).
Stir in oats, nuts and raisins; spread into a greased and floured pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana-oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together; set aside.
Beat butter, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Beat in bananas and vanilla until smooth.
Gradually stir in flour mixture and oats until well mixed.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces and place in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
(I use all white meat.)
In saucepan mix and bring to a boil chicken broth and soup.
In another bowl combine melted magarine, flour and milk.
Mix thoroughly to form batter.
Pour broth mixture over chicken.
Spoon batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan according to the directions on the box.
Boil pineapple and sugar for 2 minutes. When cake is done, punch holes in cake with a round wooden spoon while the cake is still hot.
Pour pineapple mixture over cake and let cool.

title: fruit cream cheese pie
directions: Blend Eagle brand condensed milk and lemon juice. Beat cream cheese until smooth, add egg yolks, one at a time beating well. Add fruit and mix gently. Fold into Eagle brand mixture. Pour into cool pastry shell. Beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually add sugar and beat until peaked and stiff. Pile egg whites on pie filling. Bake in slow oven (325°) 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: creamy clam chowder
directions: Heat potatoes, shallots, broth and garlic to boiling in Dutch oven; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer about 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Cool slightly.
Place 1/2 of potato mixture in blender, cover and blend about 15 seconds or until smooth.
Stir back into potato mixture in Dutch oven.
Stir in milk, pepper, the clams and bacon.
Heat over medium heat, stirring frequently, until hot.
Sprinkle with chives.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in tube pan.
Place in cold oven and set temperature at 325°.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: dad's bread
directions: Mix yeast, water and 2 tablespoons sugar in a glass. Let set for 10 to 15 minutes. In large roaster, mix 8 cups water, Crisco, 8 tablespoons sugar, salt and flour. Add water with yeast, then add more flour until it doesn't stick to hands. Add flour a little at a time. Cover with towel. Let rise in warm place until doubled in size; knead.
Coat bottom of pan and top of dough with grease. Let rise.
When doubled in size, knead again. Put in loaf pans. Let rise until double again. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Let stand 20 minutes before cutting.

title: pineapple cake dessert
directions: Bake cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat 8 ounces cheese with 1/2 cup milk.
Add 1 cup milk.
Beat well and add pudding mix. Beat
well and pour on top of cake.
Add drained pineapple (crushed).	Top
with
whipped cream and sprinkle nuts on top.

title: uncooked chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter and add vanilla.
Add cocoa and mix well.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix until well blended and forms a large ball.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Let set in refrigerator until almost solid.
Cut before it gets too hard in squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: bean and bacon soup
directions: Rinse beans and soak in 3 quarts water.
Fry bacon until crisp and add to beans.
Cook onions in bacon drippings until soft.
Add to beans along with drippings.
Add all the other ingredients. Boil soup to a boil until vegetables are soft.
Remove bay leaf. Put in jars and pressure cook 10 pounds for 30 minutes.

title: carrot pineapple muffins
directions: Combine sugar, oil and beaten eggs.
Flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt should be mixed separately and well.
Then add these dry ingredients to the sugar, oil, egg mixture and stir just to moisten.
Add grated carrots, pineapple and vanilla.
Fill muffin cups (with liner) 3/4 full and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Chopped nuts are a nice addition.
Yields about 10 muffins.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place
ribs in a baking dish, meaty side
up.
Place
a slice of lemon and a thin slice of onion.
Roast
at
450° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring
to
a boil and pour over ribs.
Bake at 350° for about 45
to 60 minutes, until tender.
Baste with sauce every 15 minutes.
If sauce is too thick, add water.

title: white fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Add to sugar and cornstarch in a large bowl.
Beat for 4 to 5 minutes; add flavoring.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Makes approximately 3 pounds.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut potatoes and carrots into medium cubes and mix with other ingredients in a large crock-pot.
Add 2 cups water, tomato paste and beef stock.
Cook on low for eight to ten hours.
Serves four.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together sugar and peanut butter. Melt chocolate. Pour chocolate into muffin pan about halfway. Spoon in a spoon of sugar and peanut butter mixture on chocolate and then more chocolate on top. Do all 12 cups and chill until firm. (They work better if you use cupcake papers.)

title: enchilada bake
directions: Cook beef, salt, pepper and garlic salt together until brown. Drain grease; add mushroom soup, celery soup, milk, peppers and enchilada sauce.
Cook to a boil.
Smash chips; place in bottom of a baking dish.
Pour mixture in dish.
Pour cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Spread meat in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with frozen vegetables.
Spread soup (undiluted) over vegetables.
Arrange Tater Tots over top to cover.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in small bowl or cup (to soften).
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved; set aside. Mix together sugar, cocoa, vanilla and heavy cream; beat on medium until stiff.
Add gelatin mixture, pour into pie crust and chill overnight.

title: fat-free brownie oat cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheets with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla. Stir just until dry mixture is moistened.
Batter will be thick. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or until set.
Cool 5 minutes on cookie sheet.
Remove.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Beat well. Stir in chips; set aside.

title: oven barbecued spareribs
directions: Roll small pieces of spareribs in flour; brown in butter.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° or 350° until firm.

title: mazie's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until soft; drain.
Put layers of macaroni, cheese and butter to top of greased casserole.
Cover with milk.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until browned.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix together butter, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Let stand 1 hour and then shape into balls.
Dip into chocolate chips, melted with paraffin.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground meat, onions and green pepper in oleo over medium heat.
When browned, drain well.
Mix all ingredients in baking dish/pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggplant caviar
directions: Wash eggplant and bake in moderate (375°) oven for about 45 minutes.
Run cold water over it.
Peel carefully and dice.
Peel onion, garlic and tomatoes; chop well.
Mix with eggplant.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Chill well before serving with crackers.

title: hot crab puffs
directions: Blend butter, cheese and mayonnaise.
Add garlic, salt, dill and crab.
Mix well.
Split muffins into 12 halves.
Spread mixture evenly on halves.
Cut each half into 6 triangles.
May put on baking sheet and freeze at this point and then put into a plastic bag to use on another day.
Broil until puffed and golden brown, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve.
Can garnish with small shrimp and sprinkle with dill, if desired.
This is a favorite of everyone I have ever served it to.

title: mock lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add butter, salt, water and Prego sauce; set aside.
Mix Ricotta cheese, eggs and oregano; set aside.
Layer 1/3 of meat sauce; top with half noodles, half of Ricotta mixture, half Mozzarella cheese, 1/3 meat sauce, 1 cup noodles, rest of Ricotta mixture and rest of the sauce.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover, then top with remaining Mozzarella cheese and cook 15 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Dice all apples.
Sprinkle apples with lemon juice to stop them from turning brown.
Combine apples, celery and walnuts. Stir in just enough mayonnaise to coat lightly.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: date bars
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add oil.
Add dates and nuts. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add.
Mix well after each addition.
Spread in greased square pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.
Roll in powdered sugar, if desired.

title: stroud peanut corn scallop
directions: Stir peanut butter to soften.
Blend in corn, then eggs.
Stir in bacon and pepper.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for about 45 minutes, or until firm in center.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: caramels
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, butter and 1/2 cup cream.
Bring to boil stirring constantly, then add 1/2 cup cream and cook slowly to 240° for very soft caramels and 255° for hard caramels.
Remove from heat and add nuts if desired and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Score into squares when nearly cooled.
Cut when cold.
Wrap each caramel in waxed paper.
Keep in airtight container.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni in 2-quart salted boiling water for 12 minutes. Rinse with cold water and drain.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Chopped olives, onions and green peppers may be added. Refrigerate 1/2 hour before serving, even better overnight.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thaw crusts and 2 tops (remove one from the second package then return crusts to freezer) according to package directions.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: ritz delights
directions: Cook cheese and milk until thick.
Add 1 cup chopped dates. Spread on Ritz crackers.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.

title: town and country pie
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and spread in a pie plate like pie dough.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: individual cherry cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add milk and egg yolks, beating until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and set aside.
Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks; fold in egg whites in lemon mixture.

title: blueberry marshmallow pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with butter. Top with crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 40 minutes longer.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, sugar and nondairy whipped topping.
Spread over cold crust.
Mix pudding mix and milk. Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remainder of whipped topping and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: rhubarb freezer jam
directions: While rhubarb is hot, add sugar and jello.
Stir well.
Pour into containers and let set.
Put in freezer.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add salt, garlic and 2 tablespoons of parsley.
Mix well.
Arrange shrimp in a single layer.
Bake for 5 minutes and turn shrimp. Sprinkle with lemon peel, lemon juice and remaining parsley.
Bake for 10 minutes and serve.

title: ann's confetti bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine soup, milk, mayonnaise and cheese, then fold in cooked vegetables and mushrooms.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop fine.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook sausage, onions and chopped stems until browned and vegetables are tender; stir to separate.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/4 cup sauce, bread crumbs and cheese. Spread remaining sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Fill caps and place in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: quick ham and bean soup
directions: In food processor or blender, coarsely chop carrots, celery, onion and ham.
In a 3-quart Dutch oven, heat just enough oil to lightly coat bottom of pan.
Saute ham and vegetables, but do not brown.
Add water and bay leaf; bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer and add beans (with juice).
Cover and simmer on very low heat for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Use salt and pepper if needed.
This soup is better the next day.

title: old fashion tapioca pudding
directions: Over medium heat in heavy saucepan, cook the milk and tapioca until tapioca is clear.
Mix egg yolks and sugar in a medium bowl. Add milk mixture to egg mixture, a little at a time.
Return to saucepan and cook until thick. Remove from heat. In another bowl (large), beat egg whites until stiff. Fold milk mixture into egg whites, a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Refrigerate.

title: spinach ring
directions: Make a white sauce with milk, butter, flour and cheese.
Add eggs, spinach and bread crumbs.
(After cooking the spinach, pat it in paper towels to remove some of the water.)
Grease a ring mold.
Put mold in pan of boiling water and bake 1/2 hour in 425° oven.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixer and beat well.
Put in a casserole dish and add topping.

title: double flaky apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon; fold in apples.
Place 1 tablespoon margarine on top crust.
Bake at 350° until golden brown on top.

title: quick broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute margarine in pan, then add the shredded carrot, onion and fresh broccoli; set aside.

title: grandma's oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand 20 minutes.
(If quick cooking, 15 minutes is good.)
Cream together sugar and shortening; add eggs, salt, cinnamon and baking soda, then mix. Add flour and mix.
Put oats in mixture and mix.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dumplings(perfect accompaniment for chicken or beef stew)
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir onion and celery in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in about 1/3 of the bread cubes. Turn into deep bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Stuff turkey just before roasting.
Makes 9 cups (enough for 12-pound turkey).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Peel broccoli stalks and slice horizontally.
Cut flowerets into small pieces.
Add raisins and chopped onion.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; stir.

title: streamlined cassoulet
directions: In a 5 or 10-quart pan over high heat, combine onion, carrots, bell pepper, garlic and 1/2 cup water.
Stir often as vegetables begin to wilt.
Add more water if needed.
Continue to cook until vegetables are thoroughly softened.
Add tomatoes, broth, wine, thyme, bay leaf, pepper and liquid pepper; simmer covered for 45 minutes to blend flavors.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together until crumbly.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: orange cheesecake(microwave)
directions: For crust, in a 7-inch pie plate, cook butter or margarine, uncovered, on 100% power for 45 to 60 seconds or until melted. Add crushed graham crackers and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Stir until all is moistened.
Press mixture firmly against bottom and sides of pie plate.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes; give half turn after 30 seconds.
Set aside.
Cook cream cheese in bowl, uncovered, on 50% power for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in beaten egg, 1/3 cup sugar and sour cream until smooth.
Add orange peel, orange juice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into crust and cook on 50% for 8 to 10 minutes, 1/4 turn every 2 minutes.
Cool. Cook orange marmalade on 100% for 30 to 60 seconds.
Spoon over top of cheesecake.
Cool for 3 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat together with mixer the cream cheese and mayonnaise. Heat (do not boil) tomato soup until warm and add to the above. Add remaining ingredients and mix together with spoon.
Chill overnight.
Serve on crackers.

title: hearty winter minestrone
directions: Shape sausage into 3/4-inch meatballs or can brown ground beef and sausage.
Stir meat often while browning in the oil.
Spoon off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add vegetables.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add broth, soups and water.
Heat to boiling.
Add pasta.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 10 minutes or until pasta is done, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 6 cups or 4 servings.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands and shape in pan.
Cook at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Last 5 minutes, spread ketchup on top.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Batter will be very thick.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake in a 325° oven for 60 minutes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as package directs and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
After cake cools a few minutes, punch holes in top with handle of wooden spoon.
Pour milk over cake.
Heat the caramel topping in the microwave 1 minute so that it pours easily.
Pour over cake.
Spread whipped topping on top.
With knife handle, crush the candy bars while still in wrappers.
Sprinkle over top. Refrigerate.

title: toot's pound cake
directions: Start with a cold oven.
Do not preheat oven.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together; add eggs one at a time, mixing thoroughly.
Add flour and milk alternately, mixing well.
Add extracts and mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sassafras muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend milk, honey, sassafras powder and sugar thoroughly.
Combine with sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs and shortening and mix very lightly and quickly. Bake in well-greased muffin pans for about 20 minutes.
Makes 18 to 20 muffins.

title: grandmom's cornbread
directions: Combine meal, flour, sugar and salt.
Mix together.
Pour 3 cups boiling water over flour mixture and margarine.
Mix well, eliminating any lumps.
Add 1 cup milk and 2 eggs last.
Mix and pour into a greased and floured 12 x 8-inch pan or small Bundt pan. Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until brown.
Pour 4 ounces water over top of pan when you take from oven.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Shape into balls with tablespoon, adding more milk if needed.
Brown in hot skillet until nearly cooked.
Add to meat.
Add 2 cups hot water in skillet. Salt water to taste.
Pour over meatballs.
Cook on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: molasses-raisin brown bread
directions: Spray a 2-cup glass measuring cup with cooking spray; set aside. Combine first 7 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat with a mixer on low speed for 30 seconds.Stir in raisins. Pour half of batter into measuring cup. Cover each cup loosely with wax paper. Microwave at medium (50% power) 5 to 7 minutes or until edge is no longer doughy, rotating a half-turn after 3 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes. Turn loaf out onto a wire rack. Repeat procedure with remaining batter. Cool. Cut each loaf into 6 round slices. This bread is great served with cream cheese. Makes 2 loaves or 12 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients, vanilla, bananas and nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: our famous meat loaf
directions: Beat thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips bacon if you like that flavor.
Pour over all 4 ounces tomato sauce.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Serves six.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie plate 2/3 full with sliced apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Mix oleo, eggs, sugar and flour together; add vanilla.
Beat good and pour over sliced apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: heavenly lasagna
directions: Spray skillet with nonstick spray.
Brown ground turkey.
Add spaghetti sauce and 3 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Use 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Cover bottom with tomato sauce. Cut Velveeta in long sticks.
Put 1 cheese stick and roll in tortilla and place in pan.
Fill pan.
Cover with chili; sprinkle with onion.
Cover with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Place diced chicken in 3 qt. shallow casserole dish; top with broccoli. Mix soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise and curry powder; pour over chicken and broccoli; sprinkle herb dressing over top. Pour melted butter over all and cook at 350° for 30 minutes. Cover lightly with aluminum foil to keep topping from browning too rapidly. Serves 12.

title: sunday brisket
directions: Before going to
bed for evening (10-10:30), put roast in crock-pot, fat side up.
Mix gravy and water and pour over roast. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and turn pot on low.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all five ingredients together.
Chill overnight. This allows marshmallows to sweeten the salad.

title: bread sticks
directions: Mix warm water, sugar and yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Then add salt and flour.
Let rise 1 hour. Punch down and knead dough 15 minutes. Then roll out and cut into finger size strips.
Dip each strip in butter and place in baking pan.
Let rise 1 hour or more.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: cherry scrumptious
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and pecans. Press lightly into 9 x 13 pan, building up sides. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Spread cherry filling over crust while warm. Mix sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over cherries. Mix sour cream and egg yolks and spoon over cherries. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 12.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cut onions into thin rings.
Place in 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish, covering bottom of pan.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips over onions.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of chips.
Mix soups and milk until smooth.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poor man's oyster stew
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add oysters, milk and water.
Bring to a slight boil.
Add saltines (for desired consistency) and salt and pepper to taste.
(For thinner stew, you may add more milk or water.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add Karo and egg, then vanilla and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° until pie is firm.

title: 2 egg yellow cake
directions: Mix together and cook in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed shrimp
directions: Saute peppers and onion in oil and butter.
Add parsley; mix with bread crumbs.
Blend with mayonnaise.
Add chopped sea fingers.
Put 1 tablespoon stuffing on each shrimp.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° until done.

title: banana nut bread(diabetic)
directions: Sprinkle sweetener over bananas; blend well.
Blend in eggs. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to banana mixture.
Do not overmix.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour batter into greased 4 x 7-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until done.

title: pork chops with dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on pork chops.
Grease the pan slightly and place pork chops close together.
Add 1/2 cup water and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in order listed.
Pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch or 11 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over filling. Pour melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until knife comes out clean.
For 11 x 15-inch pan, bake at 375°.
Serve warm or cold; plain or with whipped topping.

title: ham-spinach quiche
directions: Cook spinach and drain well. Saute onion in butter.
Mix milk and eggs.
Add to spinach.
Place ham and cheese on bottom of pastry shell.
Pour other ingredients on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix everything together.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° about 1 hour (until it begins to lose liquid).
Keep covered about half of baking time, then uncover to brown.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, peanut butter, oil, water, and eggs; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a bowl.
Store in a container with lid until ready for use.
Serve with your favorite vegetables.

title: venison cacciatore
directions: Marinate the venison in the wine (red vinegar may be substituted), olive oil, salt and pepper to taste.
Remove the meat the next day and save the marinade.
Saute meat in oil in a large skillet until browned on both sides.
Remove from skillet and saute garlic.
Add meat, tomatoes, parsley, mushrooms, basil, marinade and basil.
Simmer for about an hour or until meat is tender.

title: chocolate rocky road brownies
directions: Make your favorite brownie recipe according to directions and bake in 9 x 13 pan.
When done, add marshmallows and return to oven for 3 minutes.
Meanwhile melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut better and pour over rice krispies.	Pour over brownies and refrigerate to cut.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Toast sesame seed and almonds together for 5 minutes at 350°. Mix with Top Ramen noodles, crushed up very fine (uncooked).
Mix flavor packet, sugar, salt, vinegar and oil together for dressing. Mix all together and serve.

title: carrot cheese ring
directions: Add butter to hot, mashed carrots. Combine all other ingredients. Mix well and pour into a greased ring mold. Set in pan of hot water. Bake at 325° about 40 minutes or until firm. Turn onto hot platter. Fill center with cooked, buttered peas.

title: christmas pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Drain cherries and pineapple (save pineapple juice and add enough water to make 1 cup).
Add color to cherries.
Combine vanilla, cherries, pineapple and cup of juice, sugar and cornstarch.
Heat until just comes to a boil. Cool. Add nuts and bananas.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip. Makes 2 pies.

title: monkey bread snack
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cut each biscuit into 4ths.
Coat each biscuit piece in the 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and place in Bundt pan.
Pour the melted butter over the biscuits.
Mix the 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon together and pour over top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Leave in Bundt pan 10 minutes, then invert onto plate.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Cook ground chuck, bacon and onion until meat loses color and onions are tender. Drain fat. Drain liquid from all beans except pork and beans. Combine beans, meat and onion mixture and barbecue sauce. Add more barbecue sauce if needed. Put in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours on low heat. You may also bake in a low oven, 200° to 250° for a couple of hours.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water, butter and salt in large saucepan. Cook until sugar is dissolved. Cook without stirring until it reaches hard ball stage. Add vanilla.
Stir gently just until thoroughly mixed. Put popcorn in big bowl; pour hot syrup over popcorn. Mix well with spoon. Wet hands and shape into 12 balls.

title: autumn fish stew
directions: Remove frozen fish
fillets
from freezer, let stand at room temperature 15 minutes to thaw slightly.
Meanwhile, in a 4-quart saucepan
over
medium
heat,
in
hot salad oil, cook onion until tender.
Stir
in
tomatoes with their liquid and potatoes, salt, basil, pepper and sugar.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring
occasionally. With
sharp
knife,
cut fillets into bite-size
chunks,
add fish
and frozen vegetables to tomato mixture, over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes or until fish is tender.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Melt chocolate and oleo. Add Equal and dash of cinnamon. Add eggs, flour, vanilla and chocolate extract, beating until smooth. Spray an 8-inch glass pie pan with nonstick spray. Dust pan with cocoa. Pour mixture in. Bake 10 to 12 minutes (center will be runny). Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Serve with whipped topping if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: no bake cherry cream pie
directions: In large bowl mix together (with electric mixer) cream cheese, Cool Whip and vanilla until all lumps are gone.
Add sugar and beat for 1 minute.
On very low speed, mix 3/4 of the cherry pie filling until well blended.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill at least two hours.
Upon serving, add one teaspoon of the leftover pie filling to the top of each piece of pie.

title: crab cakes
directions: Blend well and pour over crab meat.
Form into cakes and put in fridge for at least 1 hour on a nonstick surface until cakes are firm.
Beat 2 eggs.
Dip each cake in egg then roll in bread crumbs.
Return to fridge for at least another hour or until ready to fry.
Fry in 1/4 to 1/2 inch hot vegetable oil until golden brown.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Shape into rolls.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake at 350°.

title: frozen party salad
directions: Gradually add dressing to cream cheese, mixing well.
Stir in fruit, sugar and food coloring.
Fold in whipped cream and marshmallows. Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Freeze.
Unmold on platter.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: yum yum cake(low calorie)
directions: Layer angel food cake in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle pineapple on top of cake.
Mix Jell-O with milk.
Pour on top of pineapple.
Slice bananas on top of pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: finger sandwiches
directions: Process all ingredients except bread and watercress in food processor or blender until smooth; refrigerate in quart size Ziploc storage bag overnight for flavors to blend.
Cut cocktail bread using cookie cutters.
Spread about 1 1/2 tablespoons cheese mixture on half the bread slices; top with watercress and remaining bread slices.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger; dump off excess grease. Add beans, tomato sauce and chili powder. Onion and green pepper can be cooked with hamburger or put in with other ingredients later. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: roach balls
directions: (I use Roach Away Boric Acid from Wal Mart.)
Use enough water to make a stiff dough.
Make into egg size balls and place around the house where the critters have been seen.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oatmeal, let stand while you cream eggs, sugar, cooking oil and brown sugar. Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Mix all ingredients and pour in 9 x 13 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake in oven at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well and mix with other ingredients.
Top with cheese.
Cover with bread crumbs or Pepperidge Farm mix.
Dot with butter and bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put margarine, sugar and milk in heavy large pan.
Bring to boil.
Cook
to 7 minutes.
Pour over chocolate drops in bowl. Beat with electric mixer until thick.
Nuts may be added before pouring into dish to chill.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add mayonnaise and water.
Mix until smooth.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans in moderately hot oven (375°) for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm in center.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together; blending well.
Place in a foil-lined baking dish.
Cover meat loaf with foil until well wrapped.
Add some water in the bottom of baking dish to tenderize.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mamie's million dollar fudge
directions: Combine semi-sweet chocolate pieces, sweet cooking chocolate, marshmallow cream and walnuts in large bowl.
Combine sugar, salt, butter and evaporated milk in large heavy saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Pour at once over chocolate mixture in other bowl.
Pour into buttered shallow pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Let stand a few hours to set.
Cut and store in tightly covered metal box.

title: martha's marvelous muffins
directions: Stir first 11 ingredients together.
Pour water over baking soda.
Let cool.
Cream honey and shortening together.
Beat eggs into honey mixture one at a time.
Add buttermilk and cooled soda water to the honey mixture.
Add dry ingredients to wet.
Covered tightly it will last several days in the refrigerator for fresh bran muffins for breakfast.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef, celery and onions.
Drain.
Mix in soups and place in an 11 x 14-inch baking pan.
Put Tater Tots over top and bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches, saving syrup.
Combine syrup, sugar and vinegar.
Mix real good.
Add cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Bring this to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove meat and add to 1 quart broth.
Bring to boil.
Mix flour, butter and baking soda together.
Cut through with milk until pastry consistency.
Slowly drop dumplings in. Simmer with cover on 20 minutes.
