Add remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes, drain.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, cheese and eggs.
Stir in broccoli.
Pour into greased baking dish. Sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Boil chicken breasts in seasoned water until well done (about 45 minutes).
Cool and dice chicken.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Mix well. Add Cool Whip.
Blend into mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill 3 or 4 hours or overnight.

title: double chocolate mint dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat flour, sugar, butter, eggs and syrup until smooth.
Pour into pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
(Top may still appear wet.) Cool completely in pan.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tortillas and cheese; heat through. In greased casserole dish, about 2 1/2-quart, put soup mixture on bottom. Add a layer of tortillas, soup mixture, then layer again until you get rid of mixture.
When layered, add grated cheese and put in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: pot roast and onions
directions: Dredge meat in flour and brown in margarine.
Remove meat. Slice onions in baking dish and put meat on top.
Add water and soy sauce.
Cover and bake 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: after church stew
directions: Place beef (no need to brown it) in 3-quart casserole. Sprinkle with salt, basil and pepper.
Top with celery, carrots and onions.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over meat and vegetables, coating all pieces.
Cover tightly.
Bake in slow 300° oven 3 hours.
Add potatoes and bake 45 minutes longer. Makes 5 servings.
May be doubled and tripled for a hungry crowd.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Chop onion into beef.
Cook until onion is clear.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until bread crumbs are brown.

title: butter carrot sticks with parsley
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, clean and cut carrots into carrot sticks, then cut sticks two inches long.
In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan over high heat and 1 inch of salted water, heat carrots to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and stir in sugar, parsley and margarine.
Mix well. Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini and green rice
directions: Slice zucchini into 1/4-inch rounds.
Steam until done, but still firm.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix rice with lemon juice, parsley and seasonings.
In a greased casserole, make a layer each of rice mix, cottage cheese and zucchini.
Top with grated cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple jacks
directions: Beat water and egg yolks together.
Mix flour, oleo, salt, baking powder, water and egg yolks like crust.
Mix sugar, 1/3 cup flour and cinnamon and pour over apples to coat.
Roll crust, put on cookie sheet (with sides) and fill with apple mixture.* Top with crust, prick with fork and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Dribble confectioners sugar icing when removed from oven while warm.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning mix. Spread onto bottom of 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish. Layer remaining ingredients over bean mixture; cover. Refrigerate several hours or until chilled. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tuna pate
directions: Blend cream cheese, chili sauce, parsley, onion and hot sauce. Add tuna; mix well and press firmly in a 4 cup serving bowl. Chill 4 hours.
Unmold and serve with crackers.
Yields 4 cups.

title: leek soup
directions: To rinse leeks clean, cut 4 lengthwise sections, then rinse. Chop up.
Saute slowly the leeks and onion in margarine.
Add potatoes, carrot, cabbage, broth, bouillon, parsley and seasoning. Simmer until vegetables are soft.
Add milk, but don't boil, just lightly simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve.
Serves 6.

title: braised green squash
directions: Saute onions in oil until tender.
Add squash and stir a few times.
Add tomatoes, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer. Cooking time is 30 minutes.

title: smothered green cabbage
directions: Melt butter and bacon drippings in large saucepan.
Add cabbage; cook and stir until tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Add garlic, caraway, salt and pepper.
Stir in soup; heat and serve. Yields 8 servings.

title: date nut balls
directions: Combine dates and margarine. Heat over low heat until melted. Add sugar, egg and nuts. Cook 10 minutes over moderate heat. Spread Rice Krispies on a platter. Add vanilla to mixture and pour over Rice Krispies and work together. Make into balls and roll in coconut.

title: corn bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add cornmeal, flour baking powder and salt.
Alternate with milk.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes.

title: onion rings
directions: Cut large onions into rings.
Dry thoroughly and coat with flour.
Mix ingredients well to form a batter.
Dip the floured onion rings into the batter and drain off excess.
Fry in deep hot oil until brown.
Drain on paper.

title: sour potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch squares.
Cook in 2 1/2 cups of water with the bay leaf, pepper and salt until potatoes are half done.

title: sam's cheese manicotti
directions: Stir into cooked, drained meat the next 3 ingredients.
Cover and microwave 10 minutes on High.
Use round dish.
Mix cheeses, egg, parsley and pepper together.
Fill shells with this mixture. Pour half of the sauce in dish.
Place shells in next and rest of sauce on top.
Microwave, covered, on High for 10 minutes.
Using tongs, turn shells over and cook on Medium-high 15 to 17 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine cream cheese, bananas, eggs and vanilla. Slowly add cake mix and mix well. Slowly add nuts. Grease 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: onion pickles
directions: Slice onions.
Layer onions, salt and ice in 3 layers.
Let stand 2 hours.
Squeeze hard to remove ice, salt and water.
Do not wash.
Mix thoroughly sugar, vinegar, and spices.
Bring to a hard boil, then add onions.
Again, bring to a hard boil for 3 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Yields 6 pints.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Rinse beans in colander and pick over.
Put beans in a large Dutch oven and cover with water.
Let soak at least 1 hour, adding water if needed to keep covered.
Simmer beans 1 hour, removing foam on top.
Keep adding boiling water as needed to just cover beans.
Put beans into slow cooker crock or leave in Dutch oven to cook in oven.
Add all other ingredients; stir, cover and set on low in slow cooker or 300°, covered, in oven; oven method requires 6 to 7 hours.
Add water as necessary to keep beans covered and removing cover for final hour of cooking to brown.
Slow cooker method is best done the night before and allowed to cook, covered, all night and the next day.
They are ready any time after approximately 12 hours.
No peeking necessary as no water needs to be added with this method.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Cut lemons into small pieces, skin and all, reserving 4 thin slices.
Mix
the cut pieces with the sugar in heatproof bowl. Boil
water
and
pour it over the lemon-sugar mixture. Let stand 10 minutes, no longer or a bitter taste will develop.
Stamp down the mix with a potato masher;
strain and pour into a jug; chill. When serving, decorate glasses of lemonade with mint leaves and lemon slices.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Beat with mixer until smooth the rye flour, brown sugar, salt, molasses, Crisco and boiling water.
Let cool, then add yeast and warm water mixture (water mixed with 1 teaspoon sugar).
Stir in 3 cups white flour; let sponge 30 to 45 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups more flour, then knead.
Turn into a greased bowl; let raise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; make into loaves.
Raise again until double.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, changing over locations on oven shelves.
Makes 5 loaves.

title: raisin crumb pie
directions: Cook raisins, sugar and ginger in boiling water until raisins are tender.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Pour in unbaked crust and add crumbs.

title: ada's incredible (nut) fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Fold in sugar, dates, candied fruit, sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Add pecan meats by hand.

title: crustless fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together. Set aside. Mix flour, sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla together.
Add chocolate mixture. Mix together until smooth. Add pecans.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Center will be soft but will firm during cooling process.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: super easy cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Put everything but the cream cheese in the blender and mix for about 15 seconds. Add cream cheese and blend for 2 minutes. Pour into greased pie plate and bake 40-50 minutes. Cool 1 hour. Refrigerate until you serve.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Butter a 1-quart casserole dish.
Drain juice from pineapple and mix cornstarch with this juice, stirring until no lumps appear in the mixture.
Add the eggs, sugar, the pineapple and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, mixing well.
Pour the mixture into the casserole.
Sprinkle the remaining 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon on top. Put little pats of butter on top of the whole thing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake vinegar and herb in tightly covered glass jar or bottle. Store in cool, dry place 10 days.
Strain vinegar.
Place one sprig of fresh herb, berries or garlic clove in jar to identify, if desired. 2 cups vinegar; 2 calories per tablespoon.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish, melt butter.
Add flour and stir well.
Add milk; microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Add sharp cheese and mix in macaroni.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and American cheese.
Put in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 c. evaporated milk on top of double boiler. Stir mixture until melted. Stir in nuts. Press one half of cake mixture in a greased 13x9 pan and bake for 6 min. at 350 degrees. Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate pieces on top. Pour melted caramel evenly over top. Crumble remaining mix over caramel and bake for 15 to 20 min. Cool slightly and cut into bars. Serve.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Roll out, cut into desired shapes and bake on lightly greased cookie sheets at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine baking soda and buttermilk, set aside.
Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff, set aside.
Cream together sugar, butter and shortening.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add buttermilk and vanilla alternately with flour (beginning and ending with flour).
Mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Add pecans and coconut gently.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans or one greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake is done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: good 'n easy mostaccioli
directions: Cut up chili roll into crock-pot.
Mix in next 3 ingredients. Simmer on low 2 to 3 hours or all day! Forty-five minutes before serving, add Velveeta cheese and prepare noodles per package instructions.
Stir drained noodles into sauce, mixing well. Simmer on low an additional 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 8.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in skin; drain, peel and dice.
Add onion, salt and sugar.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Pour bacon and drippings over potatoes.
Heat vinegar and water to boiling in frypan; pour over potatoes.
Toss lightly.
Serves 4 (recommend doubling recipe).

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil, then sifted dry ingredients.
Add carrots and eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add nuts last.
Blend well. Bake in medium loaf pan at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: brown sugar pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add eggs, flour, dry ingredients and milk.
Mix well.
Add pecans last.
Pour into a tube cake pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Season flour with salt and pepper.
Dredge meat in seasoned flour.
Place onion in crock-pot. Add meat.
Top with carrots and celery.
Cover with tomato sauce. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 10 minutes and then on high for 3 to 5 hours.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Combine remaining ingredients into mixture.
Roll into small balls and bake 6 minutes at 375°.

title: southern caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Drain, place in serving bowl.
Serve with Triscuits (may be made 5 days ahead). Serves 6 to 8.

title: boston cream candy
directions: Boil ingredients until forms soft ball in cold water.
Take off stove; beat until it starts to grain.
Add 1 cup nuts.
Pour into well buttered pan.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: quick nut rolls
directions: Melt butter in an 8 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch deep classic pie plate or quiche dish.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and nuts.
Combine thoroughly.
Cook with microwave on High (100%) for 3 minutes. Stir mixture at 2 and 1 minutes.
Add biscuits to bubbling hot syrup.
With tray shelf in center position, microwave on High (100%) for 3 1/2 minutes.
Brown 6 to 7 minutes or until desired browning.

title: fresh fruit combo
directions: Combine honey, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Chill.
Mix together fruits and pour chilled dressing over just before serving.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Chop or slice all ingredients and mix together.
Use creamy cucumber salad dressing, or any dressing of your choice.

title: derby day dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Just add crackers and you are set.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix together.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Keep leftover in refrigerator, covered.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients well. Chill 15 minutes.

title: soup-er sour cream(no-fat)
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl, cover and refrigerate at least one hour prior to use.
Use as a dollop for soups, for baked potatoes or as a dip.
Sprinkle with chives, or they may be combined with all ingredients.
The choice is yours.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients with spoon until well blended.
Then beat with mixer (medium speed) for 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a Bundt pan or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat the egg white until stiff.
Beat all the other ingredients together and then "fold in" the egg whites. Top with the dash of nutmeg in each glass.

title: round steak
directions: Cut all fat off steak;
cut into 4 or 5 pieces.
Salt and pepper steak.
Roll in flour and brown.
In big baking dish, add oil and 2 tablespoons of flour; make a sauce like gravy.
Add to this tomatoes, carrots, celery and onion.
Stir until well blended and bubbly.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 325°
for 2 hours.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine and mix well the flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add milk to which the beaten egg yolks have been added.
Place over boiling water, stirring until mixture begins to thicken.
Then cover and cook until well thickened.	Add coconut and pour into a baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites, gradually adding 4 tablespoons sugar until stiff glossy peaks form.
Fold in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread on pie and brown in 350° oven.

title: extra flavor chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in Dutch oven.
Brown beef cubes. Add corn juice, tomatoes, soy sauce, chili powder and oregano. Cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours.
Uncover and simmer 45 minutes until meat is tender.
Stir in corn and green chiles and cook until heated.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Combine flour and dry ingredients; add alternately with sour cream.
Keep batter smooth.
Spoon 1/3 of mixture into Bundt pan.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle batter with cinnamon mixture.
Repeat 2 more layers.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.
Remove from pan to wire rack or plate.
Cool completely before cutting.
Tastes better as it gets older.

title: cinnamon stick pickles
directions: Day 1:
Mix 1 cup lime with 1 gallon water.
Pour over cucumbers and soak 12 hours.
Stir often.

title: blueberries with fluffy dumplings
directions: Mix sugar and water. Bring to a boil in heavy skillet with tight cover. Add blueberries. Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sesame chicken kabobs
directions: Combine vegetable oil, soy sauce, Chablis, corn syrup, sesame seed, lemon juice, garlic powder and ginger.
Stir well.
Add chicken and vegetables and chill for 2 hours.
Drain chicken and reserve marinade.
Alternate chicken and vegetable pieces on skewers, placing tomatoes on each end.
Grill 6 inches from medium-hot coals 15 to 20 minutes, turning and basting often with marinade.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place butter in 2-quart glass casserole dish.
Microwave at high setting 1 minute or until melted.
Add confectioner sugar, cocoa and milk; blend well.
Microwave on high for 2 minutes. Stir chocolate to blend well.
Add marshmallows pecans and vanilla. Stirring until marshmallows are melted and blended into chocolate mixture.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square baking pan. Cover and chill in refrigerator until set.
Cut into 1-inch squares. Makes 1 3/4 lb.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix pudding mixes and milk together with the ice cream.
Pour into the two pie crusts.
Chill until set.
Just before serving, top with Cool Whip and grated chocolate bar.

title: seafood linguine
directions: Prepare linguine as directed.
Meanwhile, in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot butter or margarine, cook onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour until blended; cook 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens slightly.
Gently stir in crab meat (broken up or flaked), Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Heat through.

title: meringue that can't sleep or won't weep
directions: Cook all, except sugar and egg whites, until clear.
Cool. Add egg whites which have been beaten until foamy and standing in peaks.
Continue beating and add sugar.
Gradually beat until very creamy.
Pile on pie and bake in 325° oven.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken, chop or shred.
Cook spaghetti.
Heat rest of ingredients (soup, cheese, broth, onion and pepper).
Mix all together with chicken and spaghetti after cheese melts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Mix nuts and sugar mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: stewed okra, corn and tomatoes
directions: Remove and discard stem ends from okra.
Cut each pod into 4 slices.
Cut kernels from ears of corn.
Peel and slice tomatoes. In a heavy skillet, saute onion in oil.
Remove from skillet. Saute okra until browned.
Add tomatoes, onion, green pepper, all seasonings and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add corn and simmer until tender.
Serves 6.

title: eight bean bake
directions: Fry and drain bacon; cut into bite-size pieces.
Saute onions in part of bacon fat.
Add Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and brown sugar.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Using a 5 to 6-quart Dutch oven, layer as follows: one-third of the pork and beans and half of the other beans, half of bacon and half of the sauce.
Second layer is same as first, except ending with last 1/3 of pork and beans and the rest of bacon and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves a large crowd.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers
crosswise.
Place in a mixture of lime and water
in
enamel
or
pottery container.
Let stand overnight. Remove from
lime
water and wash through 3 changes of fresh, cold
water.
Mix
vinegar,
sugar
and
salt.
Place drained cucumbers in mixture and let stand for 3 hours.
Bring to a boil for
30 minutes.
Place in hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: frozen strawberry daiquiri
directions: Combine strawberries, limeade and rum in blender.
Add ice cubes and liquify.
Yields approximately 10.
Can be stored in covered plastic container in freezer before serving.

title: blood dumplings(blod kompen)
directions: Once you have learned to boil and steam potatoes the Norwegian way, you will always use this method when boiling potatoes. Quickly bring thinly peeled potatoes (if extra large, halve or quarter them) to a boil and cook until easily pierced by the tip of a knife or a fork.
Do not overcook or they will become soggy and fall apart easily.
Drain immediately.
Return potatoes to a low heat; shake pan gently to prevent sticking and continue steaming until the pan is completely dry.
Remove from heat and cover pan with a cloth, not the lid, until ready to serve.
You can also add butter or margarine if you want to.

title: brandied fruit
directions: Mix starter juice, 2 1/2 cups sugar and peaches in a large one gallon glass container.
Stir daily for the next 10 days with a plastic or wooden spoon.
On the 10th day, add 2 1/2 cups more sugar and the pineapple, cut up with its juice or a can of fruit cocktail.
Stir daily for the next 10 days.
On the 20th day add chopped, drained maraschino cherries.
Stir daily for the next 10 days.
On the 30th day, drain fruit and save juice for starter for next cake.
This bakes 3 cakes.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Cook onion in water 5 minutes and drain.
Add to rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased 11 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and place under broiler for 5 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles until done; drain.
In bowl, stir soup, drained tuna, milk and grated cheese.
Add cooked egg noodles. Add peas.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn and peppers
directions: Defrost corn in 2 tablespoons butter, stirring until kernels are separated.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes over low flame.
Uncover.
Add 1 teaspoon brandy and 1 tablespoon peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken in small amount of oleo and Italian salad dressing.
When done, add cream of chicken soup, drained Ro-Tel tomatoes, sour cream and cheeses.
Simmer until all cheese is melted.
Let cool slightly, then roll up in flour tortilla shells (approximately 2 to 3 tablespoons mixture per shell).
Place in casserole dish.
If you have any cheese mixture left, spread it over rolled up shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese crescent squares
directions: Place 1 package of crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on crescent roll leaving a little space at the edge.
Top with second package of crescent rolls.
Pinch edges together all the way around.
Top with a little egg yolk.
Spread with brush or fingers.
Sprinkle lightly with brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for approximately 20 minutes. Cool; don't try to cut until completely cool.
Cut in small squares and refrigerate.
(Can be used as dessert.)

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs, then add eggs, milk and molasses.
Sift flour, soda and ginger into mixture and beat well. Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top squares with whipped cream when serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef with chopped onion. Mix can of mushroom soup with Ro-Tel tomatoes; blend or mash with fork. In casserole dish, place the following in layers: spread half of ground beef, sprinkle half of Doritos, spread can of beans over all, place 4 slices of cheese, spread rest of ground beef, sprinkle some more Doritos, pour all of Ro-Tel mixture over Doritos, then place 4 slices of cheese. Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, baking soda and vanilla; then add flour alternately.
Roll and cut out.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes large amount.
May freeze half of dough.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, pudding, egg whites, oil, water and rum.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Fold in coconut.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at least 2 inches deep for 30 to 40 minutes.
When done, punch holes in top of cake with fork.
Shake pina colada mix well, then pour over top of cake. Let cool at least 25 minutes before adding topping.

title: hershey's chocolate cake
directions: Cream all together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish. Top with 1 cup buttered breadcrumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Mix the gelatine and sugar in a medium saucepan.
Blend in milk.
Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Do not boil! Remove from heat; add chocolate.
Stir until chocolate melts, then beat with whisk until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill until almost set.

title: pickled beets
directions: Put sugar, vinegar and water in saucepan; boil for 3 minutes. Cook beets and skin them.
Cut and put in jars.
Pour hot syrup on them; seal tightly.
Let sit about 1 week.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach.
Add other ingredients after spinach is cooked, cooled and drained.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from bone.
Reserve broth. You will need 2 2/3 cups broth.
Combine chicken soup with 1/2 the broth.
Mix well and set aside.

title: chicken bake
directions: Mix ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix together cinnamon and 5 Tbsp. of sugar.
Set aside. Combine flour, baking powder, eggs, sugar, oil and orange juice in large bowl.
Beat until smooth, mixture will be thick.
Pour half the batter in tube pan, half of the apple slices and sprinkle half the cinnamon/sugar mixture over apples.
Repeat.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes in a 350 degree preheated oven.

title: snow hut
directions: Using large mixing bowl, dissolve lemon Jello in hot water, add orange juice and let set until thick but not jelled.
Fold in some Cool Whip.
Push into mixture small pieces of angel food cake until it will absorb no more.
When set, unmold and frost with whipped topping.
Garnish with strawberries.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add apples, raisins and walnuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut.
Remove brownies from pan and roll each one in powdered sugar.

title: spinach squares
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Saute onion while melting margarine (in microwave).
Mix eggs, milk, margarine, onions and spinach. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 8 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: ruthie's banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, soda and eggs, then add bananas.
Add flour and nut meats.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a preheated oven.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a medium heavy saucepan, combine sugar, water and syrup. Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, to hard crack stage or until mixture reaches 285° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add peanuts and baking soda; beat for 3 minutes.
Immediately pour mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let cool completely in pan.
Break into pieces in pan.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: baked red snapper
directions: Place fillets in a shallow baking pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick coating.
Combine onion, lemon, orange juice and orange rind and pour over fish.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes. Sprinkle fish with nutmeg and pepper.
Bake in a moderate oven at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or just until fish flakes easily.
Or microwave on High 3 minutes and allow to stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Garnish with a slice of green pepper and a sprinkling of sliced almonds or twists of lemon or a pineapple slice with cherry in the middle, or a few shreds of carrot and a mint leaf.
Yield:
3 to 4 servings.

title: fajitas
directions: Cut the skirt steak into 3 to 4-inch pieces.
Put the steak in a plastic bag and add the remaining ingredients.
Tie the bag securely and marinate in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Drain marinade and discard.
Broil the steak over coals, mesquite if you want to be authentic, or pan broil in a heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Either way, cook only 2 to 3 minutes per side. Carve into thin slices across the grain.
Serve on warm tortillas with your choice of assorted condiments:
chopped onions, tomatoes, grated cheese, guacamole, sour cream, picante, pico de gallo.

title: hungarian mushroom soup
directions: Saute the onions in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Salt slightly. In a few minutes add the mushrooms, dill weed, 1/2 cup stock or water, tamari and paprika.
Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a large saucepan.
Whisk in flour and cook a few minutes.
Whisk in milk.
Cook; stir frequently over low heat, about 10 minutes, until thick.
Stir in mushroom mixture and remaining stock or water.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chinese spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving pieces and simmer 2 hours in salt water or until tender.
Remove; drain and brown in 3 tablespoons fat. Remove ribs.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce and add to fat.
Cook until sauce is transparent.
Add ribs, onion and green pepper.
Cook about 5 minutes or until the ribs absorb most of the sauce.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: Cook 26 shells according to package directions.
Combine remaining ingredients, except for spaghetti sauce.
Stuff each shell with about 1 tablespoon of mixture.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Heat oil; cook onion and garlic.
Add carrots and stock; boil about 25 minutes.
Add sour cream and serve.
Do not boil after adding cream.

title: shrimp with spinach fettucini alfredo
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in a large frying pan on low heat. Add 1/2 cup flour and stir to make a thick gravy. Add the half & half (if too thick, use milk to thin). Season with pepper and seasoned salt. Add the parmesan and romano cheese. Sprinkle with parsley. Add shrimp or crab. Cook 1/2 large package spinach fettucini and mix with shrimp in frying pan. Serves 7 to 8.

title: cheese pizza puffs
directions: Lightly coat a cookie sheet with nonstick vegetable spray; set aside.
Separate the dough into 10 pieces.
Make an indentation in the center of each piece with your thumb.
Lightly sprinkle each indentation with oregano and garlic powder.
Top each with a cheese cube.
Pull dough over the cheese and firmly pinch the dough together so that the cheese is completely enclosed.
(This is very important to prevent cheese from oozing out during baking.)
Place on cookie sheet, seam side down, 2-inches apart. Repeat with the remaining biscuits.
Light brush the tops with pizza sauce.

title: mrs. siniard's squash pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together to the consistency of pancake mix. Cook as you would regular pancakes.

title: potato stuffing
directions: In a large saucepan, saute the onion and celery in butter until tender.
Remove from the heat.
Add bread, potatoes and parsley.
Mix well.
Spoon into a greased 1-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: If flour is self-rising, omit soda, salt and powder.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: *Mix 3 1/2 cups milk with 2 packages pudding.
Let pudding set before using.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream
together
butter
and 1 cup sugar.
Add and beat eggs, one at a time.
Mix together sour cream, baking soda and vanilla; add
to
creamed
mixture alternating with flour and baking powder
mixed together.
Put half of batter in a large tube
pan, then sprinkle with half sugar and cinnamon mixture. Marble
it in,
then
put
remainder of batter.
Sprinkle and marble again. Bake in preheated oven for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add 1 cup milk. Pour into skillet which already has 2 cups milk and butter on low heat. Bring to boil, stirring continually. Once boiling, simmer for 5 minutes. Pour over hot biscuits.

title: deer roast
directions: Trim roast of all fat and connecting tissue.
Brown meat in shortening in a Dutch oven.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Place 1 tablespoon soup mix over meat and the remainder in bottom of pan. Pour water around meat and cook, covered tightly, at 325° for 2 hours until tender.
Remove meat to heated platter.
Add flour to pan drippings; blend well.
Add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve with roast.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch pan.
Bake one hour and drain.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: original banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in 4 egg yolks and milk.

Blend well. Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened. Reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Spread small amount on bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover with layer of Nilla wafers. Top with layer of sliced bananas.
Pour about 1/3 of the custard over the bananas. Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard to make 3 layers of each, ending with custard.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Spoon on top of pudding, spreading to cover entire surface and sealing well to edges.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until delicately browned.
Cool slightly or chill.
Just before serving, garnish with banana slices, then Nilla wafers upright around edge of dish.

title: lemon iced tea
directions: In pitcher, combine tea, lemon juice and sugar; stir until dissolved.
Chill if desired.
Serve over ice.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: chocolate decadence(topped with raspberry sauce)
directions: Generously butter bottom of 8 1/2-inch spring-form pan; set aside.
In heavy saucepan, melt chocolate and butter.
Stir in sugar and water until well blended.
Beat in egg yolks one at a time.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
When chocolate has cooled slightly, gently fold 1/4 chocolate mixture into egg whites.
Repeat with remaining chocolate.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
(Cake will look underbaked.) Cool on wire rack.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Prepare Raspberry Sauce.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half of mixture into greased skillet.
Sprinkle cheese over mix.
Pour remaining mix over cheese.
Bake slowly for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oven polenta
directions: Combine all ingredients into a casserole dish and place in cold oven. Turn oven to 350°. Bake covered for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serves 2.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on packages; place in a large Pyrex dish which has been buttered.
Before starting to mix the sauce, have everything measured and on the cabinet beside the stove since the sauce can stick to the pan easily while it is cooking.

title: chicken smitane
directions: Mash garlic with sour cream, lemon juice, seasoned salt and paprika.
Coat chicken with sour cream mixture.
Cover and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Remove chicken from sour cream mixture, allowing as much as possible to adhere.
Gently roll in crumbs and arrange in single layer in greased long shallow baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over chicken and bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: squash balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into balls.
Drop into hot oil.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts and pull chicken from bone.
Cook vegetables in 2 cups of chicken broth from cooked chicken.
Add soups and English peas.
Put in pan and place crescent rolls on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until rolls are brown.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole.
Top with 2 cups crushed potato chips and 1 cup grated cheese.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken pie
directions: Spread the first 4 ingredients in layers in casserole dish.

title: cranberry-apple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Break up cranberry sauce; beat with a fork or beater until smooth.
Add to hot gelatin; mix well. Chill until partially set.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts. Pour into mold or 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Chill until set.

title: hamburger cheese casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off grease.
Add salt, soup and milk.
Stir until cheese soup in smooth.
Slice potatoes and place in greased casserole dish.
Pour hamburger mixture over potatoes and bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: diet dip
directions: Mix in blender until creamy.
Chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: rainy day dish
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
Brown hamburger in bacon grease; drain. Add soup and rice.
Crumble bacon into it.
Stir together and put in casserole.
Bake in covered casserole at 325° to 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until heated through.

title: lemon flounder
directions: Lightly coat a microwave pan with cooking spray.
Place flounder in pan.
Squeeze lemon on top.
Season to taste. Sprinkle lightly with paprika and microwave about six minutes. Be careful not to overcook.
Garnish with parsley and eat to stay thin!!

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Mix with egg, vanilla and flour. Add pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken noodles
directions: Divide dough in half.
Roll very thin.
Add enough flour so they will not stick together.
Cut in thin strips.
Cook in chicken broth for 5 to 10 minutes; cook slowly.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scald cream. Add sugar, salt and oil. Cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten eggs and yeast dissolved in warm water.
Beat and add flour gradually until of kneading consistency. Knead on floured board for 5 minutes.
Let rise in warm place. Divide dough. Roll out as a rectangle and spread half with 1/4 of the butter and cinnamon mixture. Fold other half over and repeat process.
Roll to 1-inch thick and cut in strips, 1 x 5 x 6-inch.
Twist and place on cookie sheet. Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 12 or 15 minutes. When cool, frost with powdered sugar icing.
Makes 4 dozen rolls.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 370° about 12 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of margarine until tender.
Add water, carrot sticks and bouillon.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: gin daisies
directions: Mix in a clean bucket and garnish with sliced lemons and oranges.
Add ice.
This is great for a barbecue or when playing volleyball.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Boil chicken and take off bones.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add cheese soup, chicken soup, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until smooth.
Add chicken and heat through.
In a baking dish, place a layer of Doritos and chicken mixture; then top with another layer of Doritos.
Spread grated cheese on top of Doritos.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: southern chew bread(blondies)
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add flour and vanilla.
(Add nuts if desired.)
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes in an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Do not overbake.

title: flour gravy
directions: Warm skillet on stove top.
Add enough grease to 3 heaping tablespoons of flour to wet flour.
Let flour barely start to turn brown, and then add milk.
Stir until thick.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: bonanza casserole
directions: Place egg, milk, bread crumbs and salt in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Add beef and mix.
Shape into 16 small meatballs.
Prepare potatoes by package directions.
Using a 2-quart casserole, stir in green peppers and about 1/2 of the meatballs.
Arrange remaining meatballs on top.
Bake for 35 minutes at 400°.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and brown in a large skillet.
Add pepper flakes and celery; continue cooking until celery is soft.
Drain off excess fat.

title: beef chow mein
directions: You will need 4-inch deep large frypan or pot.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Add a few cloves and the cinnamon.
Slice orange and place in crock-pot.
Serve hot.

title: sticky buns
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear 1 loaf bread into pieces and put in pan.
Mix together margarine, brown sugar, pudding, cinnamon and milk.
Pour half mixture over bread.
Tear second loaf of bread in pieces and put over first layer.
Drizzle remaining mixture over top.
Let rise 3 hours.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli-cashew casserole
directions: Wash fresh broccoli carefully and cut off the thick stems. Quarter the florets and cut the tender stems in bite size pieces. Steam lightly for 3 minutes.
Or, thaw the frozen variety and drain well.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving size pieces. Brown well and drain. Place in roasting pan. In saucepan, mix remaining ingredients and boil for ten minutes. Pour over ribs. Cover. Bake at 350 degrees for approx. two hours. Stir occasionally.

title: caroline anderson's crisp sweet pickles in an open jar
directions: Dissolve salt in 1 gallon boiling water, pour over pickles and let stand 1 week.
Drain and cover with boiling water in which alum has been dissolved.
Let stand 24 hours and drain.
Be sure to split each pickle.
Failure to do this causes shrinkage.

title: overnight souffle
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Alternate 6 slices of bread and half of combined cheeses. Repeat with the remaining bread and cheese. Beat eggs; add dry mustard and milk. Blend well. Pour over bread and cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and stir butter into hot spaghetti.
Stir in eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Press spaghetti mixture into a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
In large skillet, cook beef, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and vegetables tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Heat through.
Spread Ricotta cheese over spaghetti crust.
Top with meat mixture and bake uncovered for 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more until cheese melts.

title: ham rolls
directions: Spread ham thinly with cream cheese.
Line one end of ham with olives, touching each other.
Roll as tight as possible.
Chill. Slice thin.
Serve with small crackers.
Very small and pretty.

title: corn casserole
directions: Generously butter 2-quart casserole. Puree 1 cup of corn with butter and eggs in blender. Mix remaining ingredients and blend well. Pour in pan. Bake, uncovered, for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°. May be frozen, but thaw completely before heating up.

title: old fashioned creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, sugar, milk and salt in a 6-cup baking dish. Bake in a moderately slow 325° oven for 2 hours until rice is very soft, stirring every 20 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and raisins; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake, without stirring, until a light golden crust forms, about 15 minutes longer.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, mayonnaise, onion, water chestnuts, salt and pepper.
Partially cook the bacon.
Pour potato mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crumbled bacon and olives.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: First mix the margarine, pecans and flour. Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry banana salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into a medium bowl.
Set pineapple aside.
Add bananas to the pineapple juice.
In a large bowl, combine cranberry sauce and sugar.
Remove the bananas; discard the juice.
Add the bananas to the cranberry sauce and sugar. Stir in pineapple tidbits, whipped topping and nuts.

title: chicken and lemon orzo soup
directions: Mix the last 2 ingredients together.
Reserve to thicken.

title: chili relleno casserole
directions: Grate cheese; set aside.
Drain chilies; set aside.
Beat half and half with eggs and flour until smooth.
Mix cheeses and reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
In greased casserole dish, make alternate layers of cheese, chilies and egg mixture.
Pour tomato sauce over top and sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cut in squares to serve as an appetizer.

title: easiest oatmeal cookies ever!!
directions: Only need 1 bowl to mix ingredients in.

title: chili
directions: Saute pepper and onion.
Brown meat and drain excess fat.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Put in crock-pot and serve.

title: broccoli rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, gently cook onion in margarine until wilted.
Stir in the mustard, then the cheese spread.
Gradually stir in the soup.
Add broccoli and rice; stir gently.
Put in buttered casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Put onion rings on top of casserole before baking.

title: chicken oriental
directions: In a bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Set aside. In skillet, heat 1 tablespoon corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add vegetables and garlic.
Cook, stirring rapidly (stir-fry) 3 to 5 minutes until tender-crisp.
Remove.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon corn oil in skillet. Add chicken.
Stir-fry 4 minutes until cooked. Return vegetables. Stir cornstarch mixture.
Add to skillet. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil and boil 1 minute. If desired, serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: angel hair with broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli into flowerets; peel and chop stem into bite size pieces.
Cook broccoli in boiling water for 3 to 4 minutes, until crispy but tender.
Drain and place broccoli in ice water to cool; drain.

title: prospector cookies
directions: Blend together shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in baking soda, cocoa, vanilla, flour and milk.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Drop the dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets, leaving 2 inches between each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cookies cool before removing from sheet.

title: avocado ice cake
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pour mixture into ice cube trays and freeze.

title: grilled pork ribs or chicken wings
directions: Marinate ribs overnight or as long as you can with the ingredients listed.
Grill until done.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Drain.
Separately boil barbecue sauce with water and hot sauce.
Stir in brown sugar.
Stir continuously. Boil for 15 minutes.
Add browned beef and onion. Let simmer for at least 20 minutes.
Yields approximately 8 servings.
Total cooking time: Approximately 1 hour.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In blender, mix the sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice.
Using blender on low speed, slowly add oil, beating constantly, and continue to beat until thick.
Add poppy seed last and barely zap with blender.
Onion juice is obtained by grating a large white onion on the fine side of a grater.

title: ham-pasta salad
directions: Toss all salad ingredients with Parmesan Dressing found in this section.

title: quick jack quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting into squares and serving.

title: tuna cakes
directions: In a large bowl, mix tuna fish and seasoning.
Heat frying pan with oil.
In a separate bowl, crack eggs and mix.
Once frying pan is hot, use a tablespoon to make cakes.
Before cakes are put into the frying pan, dip into the eggs.
Allow cakes to brown on both sides.
Serve hot.

title: ham, vegetables and bows
directions: Cook and drain pasta as directed on package in 3-quart saucepan; set aside. Wipe saucepan dry with paper towel.
Heat oil in same saucepan over medium-high heat.
Cook onion in oil 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender; reduce heat to medium.
Stir in cauliflower mixture.
Cover and cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cauliflower mixture is crisp-tender.
Stir in ham, fennel seed, pepper and pasta.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until hot.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place beef in bottom of casserole. Add remaining ingredients in order given. Salt each layer. Top with 1 can cream of chicken soup and about 1/2 can of water. Cover casserole and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: rolls that don't have to rise before baking
directions: Mix yeast in warm water until dissolved.
Beat egg and add to mixture; add sugar, then oil.
Add flour and stir well.
Pour onto a very well floured surface; knead and continue to add flour until dough is firm and workable.
Pinch off; form rolls and bake at 400° until done.
This dough keeps a week in refrigerator.

title: oven barbecue beef
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Cook, covered, in a 275° oven for 12 hours.
Remove from oven and shred with fork. Serve on hot onion rolls.
Makes 25 sandwiches.
Freezes perfectly.

title: coconut pie filling
directions: Cook filling as on box but add egg yolks to mixture before cooking.
Add coconut after filling is cooked.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix Jell-O, lemon juice and water in blender.
Add cottage cheese and pour into bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust shell and refrigerate.

title: vegetable nut roast
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add mushrooms, onions and green pepper.
Cook until tender, but not browned.
Combine mushroom mixture in bowl with carrots, celery, sunflower seeds, walnuts, eggs, bread crumbs, basil and oregano.
Mix well.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour for regular loaves or 50 minutes for small loaves.

title: party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt margarine in a large, shallow pan over low heat.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt. Add cereal and nuts.
Mix over low heat until all the pieces are coated.
Heat for 45 minutes in the oven, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread out on absorbent paper to cool.
Yields 7 1/2 cups.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 225° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese topped green beans and peas
directions: In saucepan, melt butter. Add flour and cook several minutes. Gradually add milk. Bring just to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Add salt and pepper. Add mixture to egg yolks.
Return to saucepan. Add cream and heat gently, stirring constantly.
Pour half the sauce into casserole dish. Add half the cheese. Add vegetables. Finish with remaining sauce and cheese.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into baking dish (spray with Pam).
Top with additional cracker crumbs mixed with melted margarine.
Use as many crackers and margarine as necessary to cover casserole well.
Bake at 350° until firm and lightly browned.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat oleo in 9 x 13 pan until melted.
Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and pepper; coat chicken.
Place chicken, skin side down, in pan.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes.
Turn over; bake until done, about 15 minutes or longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pa's shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine molasses, baking soda and boiling water.
Pour into pie shell.
Combine flour, brown sugar, shortening, salt and baking powder in a bowl.
Blend to the consistency of coarse meal. Spread crumb mixture over the molasses mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until pie tests done.

title: frosted nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat egg whites and gradually add sugar until stiff.
Stir in nuts and mix well.
Place in large shallow pan.
Put stick margarine in center of pan.
Stir about every 10 minutes (4 or 5 times) until meringue disappears and nuts are evenly coated and browned.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Put chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain peas, onions, mushrooms and potatoes and add this to the baking pan.
Mix broth and soup and pour into baking dish.
Mix flour, margarine, pepper and buttermilk and pour this into baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl and set aside.
In a quart microwave-safe bowl, add chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal, stirring until well coated.
Pour into a large Ziploc bag with powdered sugar.
Seal securely and shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil first 2 ingredients until it forms a ball in cold water. Cream next 3 ingredients together.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Blend in beaten eggs, sour milk and bananas. Add flour, salt and soda. Blend well.
Fold in walnuts. Bake in slow oven at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Check for doneness in center of loaf with toothpick. Remove from pan immediately.
Makes 1 standard loaf.

title: basic white sauce mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container. Stir together 1/3 cup dry mix and 1 1/4 cups water in saucepan. Cook and stir until thickened.
Use as a substitute for 1 can condensed cream soup in recipes.
Equivalent to 9 cans condensed soup.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix altogether.
Pur in casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: braised tips
directions: Slice meat into 1/4 x 2-inch strips.
In electric skillet on high heat, add seasoned meat to hot oil.
Cover, braise for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Do not scorch.
Add drained mushrooms and saute 5 more minutes.
Add beef broth, simmer 20 to 30 minutes, covered.
Stir often.
Add flour, milk and Kitchen Bouquet mixture to thicken broth.
Stirring frequently, cook until desired consistency.
Serve tips and gravy over rice or egg noodles.

title: cracker candy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil and cover with a layer of saltine crackers.

title: olive roll-ups
directions: Trim edge from bread and roll bread flat with rolling pin. Spread softened cream cheese on bread slice, then place 4 whole olives in a line.
Roll up.
Be sure bread is sealed.
May use toothpick to keep closed.
Put in fridge overnight.
Then slice roll into small bite size pieces and arrange on plate.
Great appetizer.

title: baked chicken and potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Add parsley flakes.
Dice celery stalks and add to potatoes.
Place chicken on top of the potatoes. Place rest of potatoes around chicken.
Chicken can be stuffed with potatoes, if desired.
Cover chicken with paprika.
Cover chicken.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add boiling water, let cool.
Add beaten eggs, yeast, flour and salt.
Refrigerate overnight.
Make rolls next day.
Let rise 1 hour before baking at 400°.

title: dessert
directions: Squeeze lemon juice and mix with Eagle Brand milk. Add Cool Whip, walnuts and cherries. Mix all together and put in refrigerator until set.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Combine mayonnaise and water.
Add all ingredients except potato chips.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle chips over top. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream cheesecake
directions: Line a 9-inch layer cake pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Put eggs, sugar, vanilla and sour cream in blender; cover and blend for 15 seconds on "Liquify" setting.

With blender still running, remove cover and gradually add cheese pieces and melted butter. Pour cheese mixture into prepared crust and bake in preheated oven at 325° for 35 minutes or until set in center.
Filling will be very soft, but will firm up as the cake cools.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Spread Comstock cherry pie filling (or other topping of your choice).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, then simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Sauce is most effective when used the last 15 minutes of barbecuing.

title: pistachio cupcakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Then add liquids and stir until mixed.
Fill cupcakes 3/4 full.
Bake at 375°.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients well.
Put into a 2-quart casserole.
Put on top of this mixture 1 can of French fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meatball soup
directions: Mix beef, egg, bread crumbs, 1/4 cup onion and salt.
Shape into 36 meatballs.
Brown meatballs and cook remaining onion in shortening until tender; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat; stir occasionally.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy in a saucepan or microwave. Mix in cool whip. Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate.

title: three cheese and egg casserole(servings:  8)
directions: Cut cheese and margarine in cubes.
Mix in eggs and flour. Bake in a greased casserole at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool about 5 minutes before cutting.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, milk and 3/4 cup sugar.
Melt oleo in pan.
Pour flour mixture into melted oleo.
Mix peaches with remaining sugar and pour over batter.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: rice with black-eyed peas
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil; stir in rice and red pepper, cooking 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add chicken broth; bring to a boil and simmer 25 minutes until rice is tender.
Stir in peas and chopped tomatoes; cook 1 minute until thoroughly heated. Remove from heat.
Stir in parsley and sprinkle with pepper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Take off bone and chop.
Cook egg noodles in chicken broth.
Mix chicken, egg noodles, cheese and soups together.
Top with crushed potato chips and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring sugar, butter, syrup and salt to a slow boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and mix well.
Put into long pan and set into a 250° oven for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat over medium heat until pink is gone.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook over low heat until meat is just tender, about 30 minutes.
For a less chunky chili, you may add more water mixed with cornstarch (1 Tbsp. cornstarch to 2 c. water) and cook it longer.

title: chili limas
directions: Soak beans overnight.

Cook and season with bacon or ham hock. Cook until beans are done; drain and put in large casserole dish. Brown meat; add onion, pepper, garlic, salt and chili powder. Mix well; add tomatoes and sugar.
Pour over beans.
Mix lightly and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine and marshmallows over low heat stirring constantly.
When melted, remove from heat and stir in 1 teaspoon food color and the vanilla.
Add more food color if desired.
Stir in corn flakes.
Drop mixture onto waxed paper, one tablespoon at a time.
Decorate with red cinnamon candies.
Let stand 30 minutes until cool.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Melt the margarine and add the onion soup mix to it.
Stir. Break the pretzels into small pieces and put them into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with the liquid mixture.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 10 to 15 minutes.

title: frozen oreo dessert
directions: Pat 1 pound Oreo cookies, crushed, into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ice cream, softened, with Cool Whip and 1/2 pound crushed Oreo cookies.
Spread ice cream mixture over Oreo layer, then drizzle one can of Hershey's syrup over ice cream layer.
Freeze until firm and serve.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 days.
Stir and mix each day.
On 3rd day make 4 rolls.
Cover with foil with shiny side in.
Punch holes in foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread(serves 12)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into a large saucepan. Cook over medium-low heat.
Add onion. Cook and stir until transparent. Drain. Discard all but 2 tablespoons of the drippings.
Stir in flour. Cook over medium-low heat about 6 minutes or until mixture bubbles and turns golden. Stir in milk. Add seasonings. Cook until thickened. Serve by spooning over biscuits.

title: "italiano" spaghetti sauce
directions: In large pot, brown ground sirloin, olive oil and minced garlic together.
Add tomato sauce and water when browned.
Bring to a rolling boil over medium heat.
Reduce to a simmer.
Simmer at least 3 hours (6 is better).
Serve over 1 pound of cooked spaghetti.
Enjoy with tossed green salad and garlic toast. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in an 8-inch round glass cake dish in microwave, 30 seconds on High, then mix brown sugar into melted butter. Cook, uncovered, in microwave until brown sugar melts, about 2 minutes at High.
Arrange pineapple slices and cherries in dish. Prepare cake batter according to directions on package using 1/2 of ingredient amounts and use pineapple juice and water for liquid.
Fill cake dish 1/2 full with batter, cover with a paper towel and cook 9 to 11 minutes on Bake or until done.
Invert on serving plate and cool.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package and drain.
Place cooked vegetables in a baking dish and add the grated cheese and the mayonnaise, stir well.
Crush crackers and mix with melted butter, spread on top of vegetables.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix together vanilla wafer crumbs, pecans, sugar and cocoa. Blend in bourbon and corn syrup. Combine into mixture.
Roll into ball and then powdered sugar.
Keep in airtight container.

title: great beef bake
directions: Brown ground beef; set aside.
Mix milk and soup in saucepan; heat until smooth.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, start to layer ingredients; put potatoes on bottom, then some sliced onions, then beef.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then dribble some soup on top.
Layer again and again until pan is full or ingredients are gone.
Top layer should be soup.
Coat all potatoes on top with a little soup to prevent drying.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until potatoes are done when pricked with a fork.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Cut cucumbers in rounds.
Dice tomato in medium size pieces. Chop onion and mix all with enough mayonnaise to make a dressing. Season to taste with salt, garlic powder and black pepper.

title: pepper ka ka
directions: Roll up and put in refrigerator.
Cut in slices and bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: beef goulash
directions: Dredge meat in flour.
In large skillet, heat oil and brown meat well.
Add onions; cook lightly.
Stir in water, paprika, salt and garlic.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Serve goulash over noodles.

title: chablis jelly
directions: Combine wine, lemon juice and pectin in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add sugar; return to a full rolling boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars and seal (1/2 pints are the best).
Makes five 1/2 pints.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Over medium heat, bring mixture to a boil.
Cook until it reaches thread stage (230°).
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.
Beat in evaporated milk, mixing thoroughly.
Serve sauce over ice cream and etc.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: red sweet sour dressing
directions: Combine sugar, salt, paprika, onion and catsup in mixer bowl and beat at low speed.
Add slowly and alternately salad oil, vinegar and celery seed.
The longer you beat, the better!!!

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, drain and crumble.
Saute celery and onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Combine sugar, flour and seasonings; stir into drippings.
Add water and vinegar, stirring until smooth.
Bring to boil.
Add potatoes and bacon; mix.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in frypan; add soy sauce and add all vegetables. Stir to mix the soy sauce and oil all over the vegetables; add the shrimp.
Stir until shrimp is cooked.

title: fruit-top pork chops
directions: Melt oleo in a nonstick skillet.
Add celery and onion; cook, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add stuffing mix, dried fruit and raisins; toss gently.
Set aside.

title: delicious ham loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: weez's chili
directions: Slice onions and fry with a little crushed garlic.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add tomatoes and celery.
Season with salt, chili powder and cayenne pepper.
Add kidney beans about 10 minutes before serving.
Top with grated cheese when serving.

title: chocolate angel delight
directions: You will need 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.

title: chicken broccoli skillet
directions: Cook chicken in Miracle Whip for about 15 minutes; add broccoli and Velveeta cheese.
Heat.
Serve over rice.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Place bread crumbs in 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Place baking dish in pan of hot water (1-inch deep).
Bake until silver knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Serve warm with or without hard sauce or cream. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water in a large bowl. Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Let mixture cool to room temperature.
Add 3/4 cup mayonnaise and mix well.
Fold in corned beef, celery, green pepper and eggs.
Mix well.
Turn into a lightly oiled or "Pam" sprayed 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or 1-quart ring mold.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve on lettuce-lined salad plates.

title: crab imperial
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour.
Slowly stir in milk, then add next 3 ingredients. Add egg and yolk.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Add sherry and bread crumbs, parsley and crabmeat.
Mix all with 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Spread some mayonnaise on top to keep soft.
Use in chafing dish with crackers as an hors d'oeuvre or as a main dish.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place uncooked ground beef in bottom of glass dish.
Sprinkle with onion.
Add soups.
Place Tater Tots on top of mixture.
Cook in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: sweet potatoes with marshmallows
directions: Bake sweet potatoes until tender; peel and mash.
Put in casserole dish.
If using canned yams, just put in casserole dish. Lightly salt and pepper.
Sprinkle brown sugar over potatoes; dot with butter.
Cover all of potatoes with marshmallows.
Bake in a 350° oven until marshmallows are lightly browned.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain thoroughly, squeezing all water out of spinach. Mix spinach, soup mix, onion, sour cream, mayonnaise and water chestnuts. Blend well and set aside.

title: easy chili cheese dip
directions: Melt ingredients together.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the last two.
Spread into a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the corn flakes and oleo.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: irish taco
directions: Split tops of potatoes, scoop pulp from potatoes.
Place extra pulp in plastic bag and freeze (to be used later).
Mash remaining pulp in mixing bowl.
Flatten two potato shells to form "taco shells"; keep warm.
Add ground beef (cooked) to potato and mix well.
Add taco sauce and cheese.
Mix well.
Place mixture in potato shells.

title: no bake polka dot squares
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Put 1/2 of mixture in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler; cool in pan.
Whip the cream until stiff; fold 1/2 of the whipped cream into cooled melted chips.
Add 1 cup mini marshmallows and put on top of crumb layer.
Add the remaining 1/2 of crumb mixture on top of chocolate layer.
Then put remaining whipped cream on top of this.
Sprinkle with grated orange rind.
Let sit in refrigerator at least 2 hours before cutting.
So good.

title: johnnie's pea picker cake
directions: Combine ingredients for cake; mix until smooth.
Pour into one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients; spread on top and refrigerate.

title: brown sugar fudge cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt into bowl.
Add brown sugar, shortening, 2/3 of the buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes. Add the rest of the buttermilk, unbeaten eggs and melted and cooled chocolate.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Makes 2 (9-inch) layers.
Frost with Fudge Frosting when cool.

title: self-crust chicken pie
directions: Cook, skin and debone chicken.
Cut into small pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slice eggs and place on chicken. Add soup.
Combine melted butter, flour, milk and pepper.
Spoon over chicken.
Do not stir as this makes the crust.
Cook in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: brown beef stew
directions: Coat stew meat in flour; brown in hot oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add hot water to cover.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Add carrots, onions, potatoes and bay leaf.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Add more water if needed.
Remove all ingredients.
Thicken liquid.
Pour over and stir.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: make ahead whipped potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
Add clove garlic and salt to water. Mash potatoes with butter, sour cream and cream cheese.
Use mix master first, beat until smooth.
Put in ceramic, greased baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Add foil during baking.

title: cheezy vegetable chowder
directions: Note:
If too thick, add more milk.

title: antipasto by ellie
directions: Cut first 4 ingredients and parboil for about 5 minutes in a mixture of water and white cider vinegar.
Chop veggies into bite size pieces.
Puree pepper.
Add to a mixture of mayonnaise, ketchup and tuna.

title: linguine with broccoli and scallops
directions: Cook linguine.
Cut broccoli into florets and discard stem. Steam 2 minutes; rinse in cold water and set aside.
Saute garlic lightly in 4 tablespoons of the butter.
Add broccoli; stir to coat with butter.
Add scallops and cook 3 minutes.
Rinse cooked linguine in cold water.
Return to heat and toss with 2 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper.
Serve with scallops and broccoli spooned over the pasta and topped with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: mexican beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Remove, drain and set aside.
Add onion, garlic and pepper to skillet; cook 5 minutes.
Stir.
Add ham, chili powder, beans and gravy seasoning.
Stir to blend and simmer for 15 minutes.
Just before serving, crumble on the bacon and spoon over crushed Fritos.
(Pass the green onions!)

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add pretzels. Toss. Bake at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot wings
directions: Combine all ingredients together; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Liquid should be reduce to a gravy.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl, then pour into pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until set in middle.

title: date bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In mixing bowl with electric mixer on medium, combine whole wheat flour, all-purpose flour and butter until dough forms.
Press 3/4 of dough into bottom of 9-inch square baking pan; set aside.
Place remaining dough between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Roll out to 9-inch square; freeze 10 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger; drain grease.
Add water and taco seasoning. Mix all together, putting hamburger mix and taco chips in last. Mix it all together with bottle of French dressing.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Lightly coat two baking sheets with nonstick cooking spray or line

title: hurry up pie
directions: Stir lemon juice in milk until thick.
Add pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: peanut butter and fudge ice cream pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey.
Stir mixture into softened ice cream.
Spoon half of mixture into crust.
Sprinkle half of nuts and fudge topping over ice cream.
Spoon remaining ice cream into crust and again sprinkle with remaining cashews and fudge topping. Freeze overnight.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all but last ingredient well and shape into a loaf.
Place in a loaf pan or casserole dish.
Pour tomato juice or puree over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover pan with lid or foil while baking.
Remove covering for the last 10 to 15 minutes of baking time.

title: ranch-style baked beans
directions: Brown meat; stir in soup mix, beans, catsup, water, etc.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: baked beans with sausage
directions: Brown sausage good and drain fat off.
Combine with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken soup casserole
directions: Melt stick of oleo.
Roll chicken pieces in oleo and place in casserole dish.
Mix rest of oleo with soups and Rice-A-Roni. Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in 1/2 cup warm water.
Set aside to cool. Scald milk with shortening added.
Set aside to cool.
Sift together sugar, salt and flour.
Add milk and yeast.

title: date balls
directions: Melt butter
in
iron frying pan.
Stir in sugar, dates and beaten
eggs.
Cook
10 minutes and let cool in pan.
Pour over Rice
Krispies.
Add
nuts	and vanilla.
Make into small balls and roll in flaked coconut.

title: jan's strawberry pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, water and butter until clear and thick, stirring during cooking.
Add 4 tablespoons strawberry Jell-O. Cook 4 to 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Slice strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour cooled mixture over berries.
Top with Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; combine beans, soup and milk.
Put into 8-inch buttered baking dish.
Fill split in frankfurters with cheese and wrap with partially fried bacon.
Place on top of green beans in dish and bake for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly coat a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl combine first six ingredients; set aside.
In another large bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add bananas, buttermilk, applesauce and vanilla. Stir into dry ingredients until just blended. Pour into prepared pan and bake for 45 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 12.
Each slice has 185 calories with 0.5 grams of fat.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Prepare in large baking dish.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O; cool.
Pour over fresh strawberries in cooked pie shell. Top with Cool Whip.

title: marble cheesecake bars
directions: Reserve 1 cup cake mix.
Blend rest with oleo and 1 egg.
This makes a dough.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion.
Cook macaroni and add.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Boil until thick.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper; add macaroni, dressing and cheese.
Top with 1 can tomato puree or sauce.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese or Romano cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dinner pot pie
directions: Steam vegetables.
Layer pie dish with bottom crust.
Prepare gravy mix.
Mix together gravy, vegetables and meat.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover pie with 2nd layer of pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut chicken wings into sections; discard tips.
Deep fry wing sections until crispy.
Melt butter in saucepan slowly!
Pour off butter oil off top of pan, saving butter fat in bottom of pan. Mix 12 ounces hot sauce and 1 ounce pepper sauce to butter fat. Stir wings in and serve.
Caution, this is one hot dish!

title: apple dumplings
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Set aside.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Set this aside. Roll out biscuits.
Place apple slices in biscuits.
Top this with the sugar mixture and nutmeg mixture.
Roll biscuits around apples and pinch together.
Place smooth side up in buttered dish.
Bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with ice cream.
Yum yum!!!

title: jambalaya
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon and drain.
Saute onion in grease.
Mix in green peppers.
After they wilt, stir in rice. Cook on medium until rice is milky.
Then add garlic, tomatoes, bacon, thyme, salt and some pepper.
Pour in chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Add ham and stir.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients and mix.
Add buttermilk and mix.
Put on floured wax paper.
Sift a little flour on top and pat with hand to about 1-inch thick.
Cut with cutter to the size you want. (Pint jar turned upside down.)
Put in a greased iron skillet. Put grease (oil) on top of biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: texas goulash
directions: Saute onion and green pepper, then meat.
Saute mushrooms last; brown all.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add water to simmer down.
After mixture boils to consistency desired, simmer another 30 to 45 minutes longer.
Melts together with time.
Serves 4.

title: gingerbread
