directions: Mix 5 first ingredients as you would for pie crust. Set aside 1/2 of this mixture. Make hole in remaining dry ingredients; add egg, molasses, buttermilk, soda and salt.
Mix well; pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan which has been greased and floured. Sprinkle 1/2 cup reserved dry ingredients on top. Bake 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with layer
of
cups of crushed corn flakes, mixed with 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mississippi mud fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Fold in remaining ingredients and mix well. Spread batter in well-greased and floured oblong baking pan. Bake for 25 minutes. While cake is still hot, spread with marshmallow cream and allow to cool completely.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, bacon and parsley.
Mix in other ingredients and shape into balls, then brown in shortening.
When browned, add the soup and tomato juice.
Bake in a slow oven or covered skillet for 1 1/2 hours.
When done, the rice will stand out like the quills of a porcupine.

title: kim's eggplant pie
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Add flour.
Stir in soup, sugar, salt, pepper and oregano.
Heat and stir until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir half of the mixture into the bowl of eggs and return to skillet.
Add tomato, cheese and eggplant.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Great hot or cold.

title: southern favorite cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with coffee, beating well after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites to which the three flavorings have been added.
Turn into two 9-inch layer pans and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Frost with elegant caramel frosting.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat in melted oleo, salt, pepper and tomato sauce and simmer covered for 15 minutes.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Add noodles and cook 10 minutes and drain.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and chopped onions together in a small bowl.

title: cherry topped cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1 cup of dry cake mix.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil. Mixture will be crumbly.
Press crust mixture evenly over bottom and 3/4 way up sides of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: coconut icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and soda together; add remaining ingredients.
Form into a roll. Chill at least 5 hours or overnight.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices; bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Makes four 6-inch rolls.

title: pat's chili
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion and green pepper.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Let simmer on stove or crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours.

title: minted pecans
directions: Cook sugar, salt, Karo and water to soft ball stage.
Chop marshmallows and add to mixture to melt.
Add oil of peppermint and creme de menthe to mixture.
Stir in pecans until mix begins to harden.
Spread on waxed paper to cool; separate.

title: fruited pistachio pudding
directions: Combine dry pudding, topping and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Serve immediately or chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine above ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Spoon out clusters onto waxed paper or into paper candy cups.
Place in a cool area until set.

title: zesty tomato dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in small bowl using a wire whisk or fork.
Store in a tightly covered jar.
Serve on Cottage Cheese, Tossed or Chef's Salad.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add raisins and applesauce. Mix.
Add spices.
Add flour until thick.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Melt together butterscotch chips and butter.
Add graham cracker crumbs and nuts.
Mix well.
Press 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese, milk, vanilla and egg.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: halloween ghost suckers
directions: Melt chocolate chips in the microwave for 2 minutes on High. Allow to stand and cool.
Stir.
Drop by tablespoons onto wax paper.
Add 2 raisins for eyes.
Insert sucker sticks.
Chill flat for 30 minutes.

title: salsa dip
directions: Press into casserole.
Heat in microwave until hot.
Serve with taco chips.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Brown onions and garlic in enough cooking oil to barely cover bottom of pot.
Add shrimp; cook about 15 minutes over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Add water and heat to simmer.
Wash rice and add with green onions, salt and pepper; stir lightly.
Cook rapidly until most water is gone and rice starts to puff.
Stir lightly, lower heat, cover and cook until done (about 30 minutes).

title: hominy mexicana
directions: Drain liquid from hominy.
Reserve liquid and add enough milk to make 2 cups of liquid.
Add grits; cook, stirring constantly, for 2 or 3 minutes.
Mix in hominy, cheese (reserve some for top), peppers and olives.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole and cover with remainder of cheese and crushed Fritos on top.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Do not brown cheese on top. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cathy's mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter, 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and salt until fluffy. Stir in flour until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Chill 30 minutes or until firm.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Dust heavily with confectioners sugar.

title: mock baby ruth bars
directions: Mix oats, sugar, syrup, peanut butter, oleo and vanilla in large bowl.
Grease 9 x 13 x 2 pan and add mixture.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Melt in a double boiler the chips and peanut butter.
Pour over cake.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: ice cream pudding pie
directions: Prepare pie filling.
Mix with milk as directed on package for pie.
Stir in ice cream and pour immediately into pie shell. Chill until set, about 3 hours.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Add Crisco; mix well.
In small bowl, beat together with fork 1/2 cup water, vinegar and egg.
Combine the two mixtures.
Stir with fork. Divide dough into 5 portions and freeze (or make pies).
Makes approximately 5 flaky crusts.

title: almond vegetable slaw
directions: Combine buttermilk and dressing; mix.
Cover and refrigerate. Combine vegetables; cover and refrigerate.
Toss together cabbage mixture, dressing and almonds just before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Mix
all ingredients in large container. Remove tea bags. Freeze. To serve, place desired about of frozen mix in glass (1/2 full) and fill remainder of glass with Sprite or 7 UP.

title: chili-hominy casserole
directions: Layer hominy, beans, chili, onion, cheese and crushed chips in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: almond chicken
directions: Cook breasts and thighs in water with salt, pepper and celery leaves.
Simmer until tender.
Cool, bone and dice.
Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Combine chicken, onions, celery and cheese with mayonnaise and almonds.
Place in casserole (preferably rectangular).
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and golden.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring until blended.
Mix in Rice Krispies cereal.
Press half of mixture into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill.
Set remainder aside.
Mix chocolate morsels, 10x sugar, butter and water over hot water until chocolate melts. Spread over chilled mixture.
Top with reserved cereal mixture. Chill.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yield:

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine first four ingredients in order given.
Beat with a mixer for two minutes, then fold in cherry filling.

title: apple rings
directions: Melt white sugar, brown sugar, water and margarine in baking dish.
Make enough pastry for 2 pies.
Roll out and sprinkle with cinnamon and salt.
Grate apples onto pastry and roll as for a jelly roll.
Cut into 1 inch rings and lay in baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well and place in a buttered casserole. Top with dry stuffing.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well; store in airtight container.
Makes 6 pounds of mix or 30 servings.

title: canned corn
directions: Cut corn from cob as soon as possible.
Pour boiling water over corn to almost cover it.
Boil 1 minute.
Add salt, sugar and lemon juice per quart.
Put in jars while hot.
Put jars in hot water.
Cook 2 hours.
For pressure canner, process 10 to 15 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Glaze while hot with 1 cup powdered sugar, 4 tablespoons milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: bean dip
directions: In a 13 x 13-inch pan, spread bean dip.
Mix sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning together and spread on top of bean dip.
Top with remaining ingredients with the cheese last.

title: meat and gravy
directions: If using ground beef, brown ground beef, onions and peppers; drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion, salt and pepper until tender.
When tender pour off water.
Place squash in casserole dish.
Add green chili, mushroom soup and Pet milk or low-fat milk.
Stir and add Cheddar cheese soup.
Spoon over the top.
Do not mix in soup.
Top with bread, chips, cornflake crumbs or croutons.
Brown in a 350° oven about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Wash bean mix; place all ingredients in crock pot or large pot with cover.
Bring to a boil and cook slowly until beans are tender.

title: pucker punch
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: oven-fried turkey cutlets
directions: Combine egg and oil in a shallow dish; beat well and set aside. Combine breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese in a shallow dish.
Dip turkey in egg mixture.
Dredge in breadcrumb mixture.
Place turkey on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until done.
Serve turkey with commercial marinara sauce.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hurry up chili
directions: Brown ground meat in skillet; add onions.
Drain.
Add seasonings.
Drain chilies, then add all other ingredients. Heat; serve with Longhorn cheese and crackers.
Tastes like you cooked for hours.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain beans and peas.
Add chopped pimento, bell pepper, celery and onions.
Heat sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves.
Let cool.
Add salt and Wesson oil.
Pour over vegetables. Let marinate for 24 hours.
Drain before serving, if desired.
Keeps for several days.

title: chewy bar cookies
directions: Grease 15 x 10-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Press into pan.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: billie humphries bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and thinly slice cucumbers.
Chop onions and pepper.
Add to cucumbers.
Cover with salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Bring vinegar and dry ingredients to a boil.
Add cucumbers, onions and pepper and heat thoroughly.
(Do not boil.) Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet, saute chopped onions and broccoli in butter or margarine until onions are tender.
Cook rice according to package directions in 2-quart saucepan.
Add chicken soup and cheese spread to onions and broccoli.
Stir all this into cooked rice.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish with 1 teaspoon butter or margarine.
Pour mixture into this.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until it is bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: fancy shake-n-bake
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire, onion, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in mixture, then in crumbs to coat.
Bake in a glass dish sprayed with Pam for 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: matt's pimento cheese
directions: Mix together Velveeta cheese, pimentos and add mayonnaise to desired consistency until smooth.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes excellent sandwiches.

title: sweet candy pickles
directions: Fill with water and 1 cup of pickling salt for 14 days.
Drain off and wash.
Fill with water and 1 tablespoon alum for 24 hours. Drain, fill with vinegar for 24 hours.
Drain off and add 3 cups sugar the first day, 3 cups the next day, 3 cups next day for 3 days.
Leave in same jar.
Take out as you want them.
Better if they are chilled or kept cool.

title: lemon pie
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Let it partly chill.
Combine cream cheese and sugar, then add jello.
Whip milk with mixer; add to sugar, cream cheese and jello mixture.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
This will make 2 large pies.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mushrooms stuffed with crabmeat
directions: Mix crabmeat with dry bread crumbs, onion, salt and parsley. Add egg and mix well.
Fill mushroom caps with the mixture and sprinkle with buttered crumbs and cheese.
Place in moderate oven (350°) until lightly browned or under preheated broiler with the broiler rack 3 inches from flame.
Allow to brown lightly before serving.
Shrimp, finely cut, may be substituted for the crabmeat. Serves 4.

title: lattice-top chicken casserole
directions: Combine potato soup, milk, seasoned salt, chicken, vegetables and 1/2 of French fried onions; cover and bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate marbled pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Alternately add flour an milk to batter a little at a time until blended.
Beat the egg white until stiff and gently fold them into the batter.
Take 1/3 of the batter and stir in chocolate syrup.
Layer batter in tube or bundt pan as follows: Pour 1/2 of white batter into the greased pan.
Pour in chocolate batter and then pour in remaining white batter.
Bake at 300 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.
When cool, turn out and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: upside-down orange biscuits
directions: Combine butter, orange juice, 1/2 cup sugar and orange rind. Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour almost all into lightly buttered large muffin tin or a cake pan. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cut in shortening; add milk.
Stir until dough follows fork around the bowl.
Knead for 1/2 minute.

title: apple roll pudding
directions: Combine, heat and set aside the water, oleo and brown sugar. Mix flour, baking powder, 1 tablespoon sugar, salt, Crisco, eggs and milk like pie crust.
Roll; spread grated apples over dough evenly.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Roll jelly roll fashion.
Cut in 1-inch slices.
Lay flat in syrup and pour remaining syrup over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken ala chicago
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken.
In 3-quart casserole, arrange breasts.
Pour sauce over.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes to brown.

title: unbeatable fried cheese eatable
directions: Dip cheese in egg; coat with combined crumbs and sesame seed oil.
Repeat.
Fry in hot oil (350°) for 1 to 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield: approximately 2 dozen.
Delicious!

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly by hand.
Drop by teaspoon on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into greased and lightly floured loaf pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Let cool and wrap in foil.

title: peasant bread
directions: Place the yeast and cumin in a large bowl.
Stir in 1/3 cup of the lukewarm water until the yeast is dissolved.
Stir in the remaining 1 1/3 cups of water.
Gradually stir in the remaining flour.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix shredded cheese in mixer for 2 minutes at low speed.
Add chili powder and mix.
Gradually add cream cheese.
Increase mixer speed and add half and half gradually to insure smoothness. Scrape bowl frequently to maintain consistency.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until creamy.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put bread cubes on bottom of pan.
Fry and drain sausage. Place sausage on top of bread in a 10 x 1 3-inch baking dish. Blend all ingredients and pour over sausage and bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple-strawberry jello salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes. Add strawberry Jell-O and stir to dissolve.
Beat cream cheese and evaporated milk. Fold into pineapple mixture. Chill.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Mix together pineapple, Eagle Brand milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice.
Mix well and pour into graham cracker crust or nut crust. Top with nuts and coconut.

title: grated sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sugar and milk in large bowl; add potatoes.
Beat eggs; add butter.
Combine two mixtures.
Add other ingredients and mix. Pour into a 2-quart casserole and bake for 1 hour at 450°. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: pastry
directions: Have Crisco and butter at room temperature.
Pour hot water on Crisco and butter and beat well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix together and put in refrigerator.
Keeps very well.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Then add juice and rind.
Mix dry ingredients and mix with first mixture. Mixture will be thick.
Form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with heel of hand.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in baking dish.
Blend 1 cup of shredded Cheddar cheese and layer on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Put in greased baking dish.
Put a lump of butter the size of a walnut on top and bake in moderate oven 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: minestrone
directions: Heat olive oil in kettle or Dutch oven.
Cook onion, garlic and salt over medium heat about 5 minutes, then stir in celery, carrot, oregano, black pepper and basil.
Cover and cook over very low heat, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Run canned tomatoes through food processor.
Add to onion mixture, along with bell pepper, zucchini and beef broth.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Add beans and simmer for another 5 minutes.
Bring soup to low boil; add pasta.
Stir and cook until the pasta is tender. Stir in the fresh tomatoes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Stir in apples.
Turn into pastry-lined pie plate.
Dot with margarine.

title: consomme rice - arroz con consomme
directions: If using onion and bacon pieces, saute in oil.
If onion and/or bacon are not used, add rice and hot oil and stir.
Add consomme and French onion or onion soup envelope.
This liquid should cover rice at least 1/2-inch above.
If it doesn't, add another can of consomme or water.
Add salt and optional pepper and stir.
Cook, uncovered, on medium-high heat until water is almost all absorbed. Do not stir during time.
Cover (do not stir) and cook on medium-low heat for 15 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle Parmesan cheese and stir as you sprinkle it to coat evenly.
Cover and cook for 10 more minutes on low heat.
Uncover and fluff with fork.
Cover and simmer until ready to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt together.
Beat egg yolks, lemon juice and water together and add to flour mixture.
Divide mixture in half.
Roll out first half like pie crust and place in large 10 x 15-inch pan.
Cover crust with a layer of fresh sliced apples.
Sprinkle apples with mixture of 2 tablespoons flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Roll out second half of dough mixture and place on top of apples.
Bake at 450° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water (boiling).
Add mayonnaise.
When cool, add cheese and vegetables.
Turn into mold; chill to set. To serve, cut into squares or invert mold onto serving platter and garnish with green olives or other vegetable decorations.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: roll-a-coasters
directions: Roll cheese inside ham.
Place toothpick in ham to hold in place.
Microwave on High for 1 minute or bake 3 to 5 minutes at 350°.

title: green beans and onion
directions: Place ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil.
Simmer boil for 15 to 20 minutes or until beans are cooked.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: fried corn
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet.
Add corn and onion.
Fry on low heat until onions are clear.
Very good.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Put drained spaghetti into a large pan or 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Shred the Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese and spread on top. Mix beaten eggs and milk and pour over spaghetti and cheese.
Add the spaghetti sauce and top with hamburger.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and crushed pineapple until well blended.
Chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Line bottom of dish with wafers. Mix pudding and milk. Alternate layers of pudding and wafers. Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Brown in a skillet or frypan, turning to brown evenly.
Sprinkle onion, garlic and other seasonings over top; add water.
Cover tightly and simmer until tender, 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
If water evaporates, add more water. Fifteen minutes before chicken is done, cook noodles.
Lift chicken out of pan.
Blend noodles with pan drippings; arrange around chicken.

title: spanish omelet
directions: In skillet cook garlic buds on low heat to flavor oil.
Remove garlic and discard.
Add to oil the diced potatoes, onions and green pepper.
Stir and cook over medium heat until pepper and onions are tender.
Add salt, pepper and eggs.
Cook over low heat until eggs are set around edges, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain beans adding 2 quarts of water. Slice sausage and add remaining ingredients.
Cook until beans are tender, approximately 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and diced onions; mix sausage, onions, noodles, salt and pepper.
Make cheese sauce with milk and cheese.
Add to mixture.
Place in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together; mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: dingbats
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; add beaten egg and chopped dates. Cook together over low heat until dissolved.
Add one cup chopped pecans.
Cook 10 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and stir.
Add four cups Rice Krispies.
Mix well; form into small ball.
Roll in flaked coconut.
Powdered sugar can be used if you want instead of coconut.
Can be made in advance and refrigerated or even frozen for days.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Do not peel, thoroughly wash and slice zucchini thinly.
Add onions and peppers.
Add 3 tablespoons salt, cover with cracked ice (4 to 6 trays) and mix thoroughly.
Cover and let stand 3 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients, pour over mixture.
Heat just to a boil.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: sweet kugel souffle
directions: Cook noodles and strain.
Rinse.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan with noodles.
Beat butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Incorporate eggs, one at a time.
Beat in sour cream, vanilla and sugar.
Slowly pour mixture over noodles.
Do not mix.

title: chocolate nut zucchini cake
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat eggs until thick and light; gradually add sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, beating after each addition.
Add salad oil and cooled chocolate; beat until well blended.
At low speed, add dry ingredients until smooth.
Add grated zucchini and nuts with wooden spoon.
Stir until well combined.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: christmas treats(popcorn balls)
directions: Bring the first 6 ingredients to boil, then add cream of tartar.
Boil to 270° crack stage.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and soda.
Have ready 6 quarts of popped corn kept warm in the oven.
(This helps when coating the corn with the syrup mixture.)
Use a wooden spoon and stir in the syrup mixture, thoroughly coating the popped corn.
Tell everyone to get their hands ready to form the balls.
(Wash and butter hands.)
Popcorn balls can be made to your size criteria.
Some like big ones.
I make mine small and lightly packed.

title: super sunday lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna according to package directions and drain.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta, spinach, 1/2 Mozzarella, Parmesan and eggs.
Mix well.

In 15 x 9 baking dish, layer 2 cups sauce, half the lasagna, half the remaining sauce, all of the spinach mixture, half of the remaining Mozzarella, remaining lasagna and sauce. Cover and bake at 350° until bubbly (about 45 minutes).
Uncover. Top with remaining Mozzarella and parsley.
Bake 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks (slightly beaten), bananas, nuts, flour sifted with baking powder and salt, egg whites (beaten stiff) and then baking soda dissolved in sour milk. Pour into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan or 2-quart pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: rice chex dessert
directions: Melt margarine. Pour over remaining ingredients and mix. Spread 1/2 of this mixture in a 9 x 13 pan. Top with ice cream (softened), then add rest of mixture. Freeze.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
You may add more mayonnaise according to texture or taste.
Chill.

title: chicken mushroom bake
directions: Slightly brown chicken breasts.
Season with a sprinkle of salt, pepper and nutmeg. Transfer to oven pan.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, food color, water (use food color bottle) and vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients except baking soda.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with buttermilk. Beat 10 minutes.
Dissolve baking soda in vinegar and fold into batter.
Do not stir.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Turn to 300° and bake another 10 minutes.

title: yolie's wassail
directions: Cook all ingredients except apple cider until thoroughly warmed.
Add apple cider.
Serve hot.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Mix altogether and refrigerate.
Add cherries to top for color.
Make in morning before using at night.

title: joanne engelman's spaghetti sauce(also used for manicotti, lasagna and mostaccioli)
directions: Brown ground chuck, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Drain. Add sauce, paste and water.
Stir until smooth.
Add Italian seasoning and sugar.
Stir.
Bring to boil and lower heat to simmer.
Simmer 2 or 3 hours (more or less).
Stir often.

title: asparagus vinaigrette
directions: Blend all ingredients except asparagus.
Pour over asparagus in shallow dish.
Do not use metal.
Marinate overnight.
Remove from marinade to serve.

title: apple rings
directions: Put in baking dish in oven at 350° until oleo melts.
Grate 5 large apples.
Place on double pie crusts, one at a time.
Roll like jelly roll.
Cut in 1-inch pieces and place in syrup mixture. Bake at 350° until dough is brown.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Mix ingredients and add dressing. Marinate 24 hours.

title: easy crabmeat dip
directions: Flake crabmeat and remove bones.
Beat remaining ingredients until fluffy.
Fold in crabmeat.
Chill.
Yields 1 cup.

title: rolled chicken breasts with asparagus
directions: Pound chicken breasts between waxed paper to flatten.
Brush top side with melted butter.
Place 2 to 3 asparagus spears on each breast, roll and secure with toothpicks.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Roll each breast in remaining melted butter, then in bread crumb mixture.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour. Meanwhile, make sauce.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown. Drain grease.
Separate crescent rolls into triangles.
Place on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points towards center.
Spread sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Cook beans until done.
Sear pork; remove fat.
Add to beans the brown sugar, molasses, salt, mustard, onion, catsup and enough water to cover beans well.
Cook until flavor and consistency is thick (slow over low heat at 250°).

title: cube steak and rice
directions: Salt, pepper and flour cube steak slices.
Brown steak in a small amount of oil.
Drain oil.
Add soups and rice; bring to a boil.
Add browned steak slices.
Cover pan; lower heat to low. Cook for 15 to 20 minutes, until rice is tender.

title: brown sugar and cinnamon butter
directions: In a small bowl, beat all ingredients until fluffy.
This is really good on baked mashed sweet potatoes and yeast rolls.

title: eggplant dip
directions: In
heated
olive
oil,
brown	chopped garlic, celery, onion and green pepper.
Add eggplant (pared if desired), cut in small pieces (slice in eighths, lengthwise, then cut 1/4 to 1/2
inch wide).
Cook
until
soft,	stirring
in with other vegetables. Add salt, pepper, cumin and tomato sauce.
Can be served
as
a dip
for
other vegetables or corn chips.
Best served
in	a halved pita bread as a sandwich.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: wassail cup
directions: Mix together sugar, cloves,
red
hots and water;
cook until dissolved and cool.

title: peanut butter rice krispies bars
directions: Bring Karo and sugar just to boiling.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla, salt and Rice Krispies.
Pat into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together (either in a double boiler or in the microwave) and spread over Rice Krispies.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix all together the night before.
Bake at 350° until macaroni is tender.

title: swiss veggie dish
directions: Mix veggies, soup, 1/2 can French fried onions, 1/2 cheese, sour cream and pepper.
Bake in 1-quart covered casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with rest of onions and cheese and bake uncovered for 5 minutes.
You may add fresh mushrooms and extra sour cream if desired.

title: crock-pot lemon chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour, seasoned with salt.
Saute chicken on all sides in oil in skillet until brown.
Drain.
Place in crock-pot.
Stir lemonade concentrate, brown sugar, catsup and vinegar.
Cook on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove chicken.
Pour liquid into saucepan.
Return chicken to crock-pot.
Cover; keep warm.

title: country biscuits
directions: Mix the Bisquick and buttermilk together, then cut 1/2 stick of butter into small pieces.
Then take the other 1/2 stick of butter and melt in a small bowl.
Mix the butter into the Bisquick and buttermilk.
Take a small amount of Bisquick and put on a cutting board, then roll dough out and cut biscuits up.
(It should make 24.)
Roll in butter, then put in pan and bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mayonnaise, being careful not to mash.
Stir in mayonnaise, stirring carefully until well blended.
Garnish with sliced boiled eggs
and sprigs of parsley.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Mix milk, sugar, salt and butter or Crisco and let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in water; let set until it foams, bubbles, or is completely dissolved.
Add to the cooled milk mixture.
Add eggs and flour to the milk and yeast mixture; beat well.
Pull out the beaters; cover and let rise overnight at room temperature.
In the morning, divide dough in half and roll out on a lightly floured surface to circles 1/2-inch thick.
Cut each into 16 wedges; roll each wedge toward the center for crescent rolls. Place on greased baking sheets.
Cover; let stand at room temperature for 4 hours.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: bean dip
directions: Layer ingredients alternately in dish, starting with beans. Top with cheese and onions.

title: sanda's cheesy manicotti
directions: Cook manicottis and rinse; drain well.
Mix all ingredients except sauce.
Prepare a baking dish or pan by spreading 1 cup of sauce on the bottom.
Fill the shells with cheese and place on sauce in the dish.
Take remaining sauce and cover the manicottis down the center.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 400°
for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pink pickled eggs
directions: Hard-boil eggs; plunge into cold water and shell immediately. Put eggs in a quart jar.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil and pour over eggs.
Cover and cool.
Refrigerate overnight or for at least 8 hours.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash and wipe chicken pieces.
Cream butter; leave at room temperature.
Spread butter on skin side of chicken.
Shake chicken in bag with flour, salt and pepper.
Place chicken, skin side up, in shallow, greased baking pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream together butter and margarine; add sugar, flour and oatmeal.
Chill and then shape into tiny balls.
Place 3 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten each ball with bottom of a glass that has been dipped in flour.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool and remove from cookie sheet.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top of each cookie and enjoy!
Makes 5 dozen.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Boil
shrimp shells and crab boil in 2 quarts water for 20 minutes.
Drain
and
cool the liquid.
Discard shells and seasoning.
Make
a
roux,
using
grease and flour in a large heavy
pot, stirring constantly over low to medium heat, until dark
brown
in
color.
Add
onions,
bell pepper, celery and cook
until
clear.
Add green onion and parsley.
To the cold shrimp broth, add enough cold water to make 4 quarts of liquid and then add to roux mixture.
Bring this to a boil and reduce to medium
heat.
Add crab, oysters, shrimp and okra.
Season to your
taste
with
sauces and salt.
Simmer on low heat at least 1 hour.
Serve over steamed rice with saltine crackers.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Place a layer of the torn angel food cake on the bottom of a cake pan or a parfait dish, then a layer of strawberries, another layer of angel food cake and then lastly cover with Cool Whip. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving. Can be served right away, but is best 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator. Also can substitute regular Cool Whip for light or nonfat Cool Whip.

title: gingered beef stir-fry(makes 2 servings)
directions: Cut beef diagonally across grain into 1/8-inch slices.
Heat oil in wok or medium skillet over medium-high heat.
Add beef and seasonings and stir-fry until beef is browned.
Add vegetables and stir-fry until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Blend ginger, cornstarch, soy sauce and 1 tablespoon water in small bowl; add to beef and cook, stirring until sauce is thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter balls(kindergarten recipe)
directions: Mix altogether and shape into balls.
Ready to eat.

title: hominy and almond casserole
directions: Mix
all
the
ingredients,
except hominy, almonds and bread crumbs, over a low fire until blended.
Drain hominy and place
in a	buttered casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over hominy. Cover
with
bread crumbs.	Almonds may be mixed with soup	or sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Excellent with turkey, ham or barbecue.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Note:
Amount of vegetables is your choice.
Can also use frozen vegetables.

title: pecan-date pie
directions: Preheat oven to
In medium bowl, with wire whisk or fork, beat eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter or oleo, vanilla extract and salt
until blended.
Stir in dates.
Pour mixture in unbaked 9-inch
pie shell.
Arrange pecans on top.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes, or until set.

title: dreamy apricot salad
directions: Combine sugar, jello and water in pan.
Bring to boil; stir to dissolve.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit.
Set aside to cool. Combine milk and cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Stir into jello mixture, then add nuts.
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Serves 20.

title: quick and tasty cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, lemon juice and party dip by hand using a spoon or whisk.
Form mixture into a ball.
Roll ball in crushed pecans to evenly cover.
Wrap ball in cling wrap and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Garnish with parsley and serve with sesame crackers.

title: blueberry-lemon muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, lemon peel and salt.
Make a well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add this mixture all at once to flour mixture and stir just until moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Carefully fold in blueberries.
Grease muffin pan or use paper baking cups.
Fill each 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
If desired, dip tops of baked muffins in melted butter and sugar (1/4 cup melted butter and 1/3 cup sugar).
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pasties - michigan style
directions: Peel potatoes and dice.
Clean carrots and onion.
In a skillet, put 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add onion; saute.
Add potatoes and carrots; boil after adding the water.
When vegetables are tender (15 minutes), drain thoroughly.
Add corned beef or any meat that's shredded or diced; hamburger is even pretty good if very lean.
Stir mixture.
Add seasonings; let all cool to room temperature.

title: clinkers dessert
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and oleo.
Spread 3/4 on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add slightly softened ice cream.
Put cookie mix on top.
Refreeze.

title: golden carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Frost while hot.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix butter, oil and sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk; add rest of ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Sprinkle top with 1 cup chocolate chips and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread pudding
directions: In a medium bowl, mix the milk, sugar, eggs, salt, vanilla and pumpkin until thoroughly blended.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.
Mix the brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on the surface of the pudding.
Return pudding to oven for 10 minutes more or until a knife inserted into the pudding comes out clean.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Peel potatoes, cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook for 10 minutes or until very tender.
Drain well, put into a large bowl and mash until smooth.
Stir in butter, sugar, a little at a time.
Heat oven to 425°.
Have a cookie sheet ready.
Pour flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and cinnamon in a medium size bowl. Stir flour mixture into potato mixture in 3 additions, alternately with buttermilk, just until blended.
Form into a ball and sprinkle some flour on top.
Roll dough to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until golden.
Spread butter on top while hot.

title: macadamia-coconut tart
directions: Over moderate heat, melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add sugar and bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in heavy cream, lemon zest, nuts and coconut. Bring mixture back to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in bourbon or rum and vanilla extract.
Pour into prepared tart shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until the filling is bubbly, thick and golden brown.
Cool for 5 minutes, remove from pan. Serve with fresh whipped cream.

title: apple-pineapple cooler
directions: Mix all together and chill. Put one orange slice into each glass or put small slit in side and slip over edge of glass.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, water and sugar with mixer until foamy on top.
Add oil, milk, salt and egg.
Mix well. Add flour, one cup at a time. Knead well 3 to 4 minutes.
Put in greased bowl.
Let rise 2 hours or until double in warm place.
Punch down.
Make into rolls.
Let rise again until double.
Bake at 375°.
This dough will keep in the refrigerator well for a few days.

title: aunt pearl's icebox pie
directions: Put pineapple, Jell-O and sugar in pan.
Heat and let come to a simmer.
let cool.
Whip chilled milk until stiff.
Mix together.
Put in cookie or graham cracker crust and chill.
Makes two pies.

title: santa's special salad
directions: Mix; top first mixture.
Toss and serve!

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into 1-inch cubes and cook in a very large pot. Stew two days and add potatoes, carrots and celery.
Add salt to taste (about 50 pound bag).
Serves approximately 3,000 guests.
If more people show, add rabbit as needed.
Do not put rabbit in unless needed, as no one likes to find a hare in their stew.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions. Combine noodles, soup, milk, tuna and cheese. Add pepper to taste.
Heat in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crunch dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and add egg.
Stir ingredients until crumbly.
Blueberries, peaches or apples in 9-inch pan.
Crumble mixture on top.
Melt butter and brush on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until brown.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: aunt ann's fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets (do not overcook).
Slice while warm.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Let stand until sugar is dissolved.
Stir and pour vinegar and salt over beets.
Let beets sit in refrigerator. Serves 8 or more.
Sliced onion is optional.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add tomatoes and jalapenos (drained, seeded and chopped).
Blend well. Add cumin seed and chili powder; stir constantly when adding powder.
Heat all ingredients over low heat.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: no-fail fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil and grease the foil with 1 teaspoon butter; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine the confectioners sugar, cocoa and salt.
Melt remaining butter; add milk and vanilla.
Stir into sugar mixture until blended; whisk until smooth.
Stir in M&M's.
Immediately spread into prepared pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick oleo in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat eggs in large bowl and add other ingredients.
Pour into pan or casserole.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes or until solid.
Cut in squares, if desired.
Yields 12 to 15 squares.

title: tomato pie
directions: Butter pie dish.
Place crust in dish. Spread with mustard. Spread cheese evenly over all.
Cover with sliced tomatoes in single layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, let set for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with basil lightly over all.	May be served warm or at room temperature.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with mixer and pour in a graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate one hour.

title: philly simple salsa
directions: Place cream cheese on serving plate.
Top with salsa.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine mayonnaise, garlic, pickles, green olives, and egg. Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving. Goes great with fish.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Beat eggs; add flour and beat some more.
Add cottage cheese and stir in.
Cook the frozen broccoli (or use 1 pint package broccoli); drain.
Add oleo and cubed cheese.
Stir until oleo melts and cheese softens.
Add to egg mixture and stir.
Add 3/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Put in large, greased casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: joann's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and paprika.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°. Put cheese and paprika on during the last 10 minutes of baking time.
Serves 8.

title: apple mousse(russia)
directions: Stew apples in water until soft. Grate apples through sieve, add sugar, vanilla, gelatin and egg whites to apples and whip until fluffy. Serve in a glass or bowl. Makes 4 servings.

title: easy butterscotch chip chocolate cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in morsels and pecans. Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until centers are just set.
Let stand for 2 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Boil beans gently for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain and add new liquid three times.
Put beans in pot with last liquid and put bacon on top.
Mix in other ingredients and bake at 300° for about 4 hours, adding liquid when needed.

title: cherry-raisin coffee cake
directions: Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Spread the batter in the greased 9-inch square pan.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese until smooth. Add flour to mix to form soft dough. Chill at least one hour or overnight. Preheat oven to 350°. Place walnut-sized balls of dough into ungreased mini-muffin pan. Dredge a mini-tart shaper in flour and press each ball of dough to fill cup.

title: apple pie
directions: In large bowl, combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add apples to mixture.
Stir in raisins.

title: sandi's banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
After mixing, pour can of Eagle Brand milk into pudding and stir.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, line with wafers and pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over wafers.
Cover pudding with 1/2 of your bananas, sliced.
Cover bananas with 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Start over and use the rest of pudding, bananas and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Make ahead.
It makes a large pudding.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Roll out 11-inch pie crust (you may want to cook all ingredients first to know how much sugar you'd like.
I find fruit pies are better if you cook them before baking).
Add the margarine after you pour filling in the pie to the top, then put on the top crust with air slits in top crust.
If previously cooked, you may bake at 400° until brown, put aluminum foil around edges of crust. If uncooked, bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add cream cheese. Add to hot jelly mixture the marshmallows (white ones are fine, but pastel colored ones makes this extra pretty), mayonnaise, pineapple (juice and all), carrots and Dream Whip (prepared and folded in last). Chill for 2 or 3 hours.

title: almond rocca cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add egg yolk and vanilla. Mix thoroughly with flour.
Spread mixture thinly on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread on warm cookies the melted chocolate bar, then sprinkle with nuts.
Cut cookies while warm and refrigerate.

title: easy baked pork chops
directions: Rinse and pat dry pork chops.
Place in a baking dish sprayed lightly with Pam.
Mix together remaining 5 ingredients and pour over pork chops.
Cover and bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes. Remove cover and broil until lightly browned.

title: chicken and sour cream
directions: Arrange cut-up chicken in shallow butter baking dish.
Cover with mushrooms.
Add well-blended soup and sour cream. Sprinkle with paprika and cook uncovered 1 1/2 to 3 hours at 350°.

title: dirt pie
directions: Let ice cream set out and soften.
Melt margarine.
Crush about 2 cups of the cookies.
Mix together with the melted margarine.
Press and cover the bottom of a pie plate.
Reserve about 1/2 cup of the crumbs.
Drizzle some of the topping over the crust.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the almonds.
Press ice cream over the crust.
Drizzle remaining topping over the top of ice cream. Top with remaining almonds.
Return to freezer.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, butter and vanilla in a large bowl; beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Beat in sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in flour and salt just until well blended.
Spread on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center pops back.

title: marinated cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage, onion and green pepper in large bowl.
Pour sugar over top.
Heat to boiling, oil, vinegar, mustard and celery seed.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12.

title: fantasy freeze pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme with mixer until well blended.
Add sherbet; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Garnish with whipped topping and berries.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain fat.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix, and pour into greased bread pan.
Bake 375° 50-60 minutes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan or tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Pour hot sauce over hot cake.

title: green beans
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Cover with French onion rings.
Heat for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: saute of 4 vegetables
directions: Steam small whole potatoes until tender.
Steam carrots until tender (10 minutes).
Parboil asparagus tips in boiling salted water for 2 minutes; drain with slotted spoon.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
In same water, boil beans the same way.
Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: southern style baked beans
directions: Mix all beans and ham or Spam together.
Cook onion, garlic, sugars, salt, catsup, liquid smoke, Worcestershire sauce and margarine on medium heat for 10 minutes, then add to bean and ham mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple syrup.
Stir; dissolve and chill until partially set. Add remaining ingredients.	Chill overnight.

title: chocolate upside-down pudding
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa, then add boiling water to dissolve mixture.
Pour this over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serve while hot with ice cream.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler.
When completely mixed, spread into buttered 9 x 5-inch pan.

title: salsa
directions: Combine and bring to a boil; simmer until desired consistency (couple of hours).
Pour into hot jars leaving 1/4 inch head space; add 1 teaspoon lemon juice per pint to increase acidity. Process 30 minutes in hot water bath.
Makes about 6 pints.
If smoother consistency is desired, puree a small amount in food processor and mix in before canning.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix all the ingredients gently.
Use for bubbles.

title: croutons with smoked salmon, goat cheese, mustard and dill
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend first 5 ingredients in small bowl.
Arrange bread in baking sheet.
Brush lightly with oil. Bake until crisp, about 10 minutes. Cool.
(Can be made 6 hours ahead.
Cover mustard mixture and croutons separately; let stand at room temperature.)

title: holiday trifle
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions with milk. Remove from heat, stir in chopped chocolate until melted and smooth.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill.
Fold in 1 cup of whipped topping.
Cut cake into small cubes and drizzle with orange juice.
In the bottom of a deep glass bowl, layer half the berries, half the pudding and half the grated chocolate.
Top with remaining whipped topping.
Garnish with whole berries.
Drizzle melted chocolate over the top.
Serves 8.

title: french toast(low sodium)
directions: Mix egg substitute, skim milk, vanilla and cinnamon. Dip bread slices in egg mixture.
Melt margarine in skillet and lightly brown bread slices.
May be served with margarine and syrup or jelly.

title: beef cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray large casserole dish.
Cook penne pasta according to package directions.
Heat oil in large pan over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic for 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms and ground beef.
Cook until beef is browned, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in stewed tomatoes, juice, tomato sauce and basil; let simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add pasta to saucepan.
Stir in cheese; mix well.
Spoon pasta in prepared casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, Wesson oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Mix cocoa and red food coloring together; add vinegar.
Mix well.
Add this to eggs and sugar mix.
Beat. Then add flour, alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes in round cake pans.

title: best peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches into large baking dish.
Mix flour and sugar. Add vanilla, margarine and milk to make batter.
Pour batter over the peaches.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: lasagna with cottage cheese
directions: Grate Mozzarella cheese.
Lightly brown garlic, onion and ground beef in salad oil.
Add soup, 1/2 can of water and seasonings.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook noodles as directed on box.
Alternate noodles, cheese, cottage cheese and sauce.
(Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.)
Repeat twice.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool slightly.

title: orange cookies
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar, salt, eggs, orange rind and juice.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: candied fruit for fruit cakes
directions: In a heavy skillet, place pineapple and cherries.
Add sugar and pineapple juice.
Add raisins.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes, turning and stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Let stand in syrup overnight.
Place fruit in a single layer on a cake rack to dry for a day.
Turn over and let the fruit dry a second day. Cut up with kitchen shears.
Store in a plastic container.
Makes 4 cups.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Stir in taco seasoning pack.
Drain. Spread refried beans across bottom of 9 x 13 dish.
Follow with a layer of taco seasoned beef, then a layer of salsa.
Last, a layer of sour cream.
Sprinkle shredded cheese across the top.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate after being served.

title: joseph's linguine with shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp. Melt butter and cook shrimp and parsley (chopped) and garlic (almost whole jar).
When shrimp are pink, add clam sauce and heat thoroughly.
Add pepper to taste. Cook linguine as directed on box.
Drain.
Return to pot. Pour shrimp and sauce over noodles.
Mix well.
Serve with Parmesan cheese generously sprinkled on top.

title: catfish parmesan
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley and seasonings.
Dip catfish in butter, then in crumb mixture.
Arrange in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 20-25 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Serves 6.

title: heavenly hash brownies
directions: Mix butter, pecans and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add eggs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and cover top with marshmallows.

title: summertime salsa
directions: In a bowl, mix together the black beans, corn and diced tomatoes with green chile peppers. Add freshly diced tomatoes and onion.
Mix, cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours. Garnish with cilantro leaves.

title: sweet potato custard pie
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given; pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for 40 minutes, or until custard is set.

title: pumpkin pie(sugar-free, double layer)
directions: May use 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice.

title: ruth's cherry yum yum
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Set aside. Mix 1 package of Dream Whip as directed on the package.
Combine cream cheese mixture and Dream Whip mixture.

title: frosted salad
directions: Combine ingredients and congeal.

title: copper kettle carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; cool.
Take oil, vinegar, soup, salt and pepper and bring to a boil; stir in sugar until dissolved.
Add onions and green peppers to carrots.
Pour hot mixture over carrots, peppers and onions.
Cool.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: beef stew
directions: Place beef cubes in baking dish.
Add chunks of carrots, potatoes, onions and celery.
Mix together tomato sauce, water and sugar; pour over the meat and vegetables.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Scatter tapioca on top.
Seal with foil.
Place in a 325° oven for 2 to 3 hours or set oven at 200° and let cook all day. Can cook in heavy pan.

title: dean's special
directions: In a Dutch oven, layer all ingredients, potato, hamburger (raw), onion and corn.
Just as you would lasagna (with corn ending up on top).
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until potato is tender.

title: five hour (no peek) stew
directions: In large Dutch oven, layer all ingredients except last three. Combine tapioca, salt and pepper and sprinkle over stew; cover. Bake in 250° oven for 5 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
A good company meal.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. In large mixing bowl, add butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla (or orange peel).
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch morsels.
Spread dough into greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 22 minutes or until very lightly browned.
Cool and cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes about 4 dozen bars.

title: hearty pasta and red bean soup(vegetarian recipe; serves 6)
directions: In large skillet, melt 3 to 4 tablespoons butter, margarine or bacon fat.
Brown meat; add fresh mushrooms and onions.
Stir.
In large roasting pan, transfer meat, mushrooms, onions and drippings. Sprinkle with minced garlic.
Add rest of ingredients and stir until mixed.
Put lid on pan or cover with tinfoil and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake in oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until mixture is thoroughly heated and vegetables are cooked.
Serves 15.
Recipe can be doubled, tripled to serve more. Serve with fresh green salad and crusty rolls.

title: whole green pea soup
directions: Simmer peas in water until almost cooked.
Add savory, carrots and celery.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add onion and tomato paste and simmer a few minutes longer.

title: low-fat nutty pineapple cream cheese on raisin bread
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the cream cheese and peanut butter.
Then stir in the pineapple and spread the mixture on half of the bread slices. Then top each with a remaining bread slice. Makes 5 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well after each egg.
Mix to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into Bundt cake pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: end of season bean soup
directions: *Three or more varieties best.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions, omitting salt. Rinse with cool water. Spread 2 tablespoons guacamole onto each noodle; top each with 2 tablespoons salsa and 2 tablespoons cheese. Roll up noodles jelly roll fashion. Cut each roll-up in half to form 2 equal size roll-ups. Serve immediately with salsa or cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate up to 3 hours.

title: festive fruit
directions: Drain all fruit, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Mix fruit in bowl. Sprinkle vanilla pudding mix over top and add 1 cup liquid.
Mix and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Add banana (sliced) when ready to serve.

title: lawman chili
directions: Saute the garlic, onions and bell pepper in vegetable oil in a large saucepan over medium heat until translucent.
Remove onions and pepper mixture from pan, leaving liquid.
Add beef and pork cubes and brown over medium heat, stirring occasionally, and adding salt to taste.
Cook meat at least 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Add onion and pepper mixture to meat. Stir and let cook together another 5 minutes.
Add dry seasonings and again stir mixture.
Add water, tomato paste, tomatoes, fresh chile and jalapeno pepper.
Let entire mixture simmer for at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Serve with cheeses and sour cream.

title: cheese and corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in water until done.
Make thickener by mixing flour in 1/2 cup of milk.
Add to potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer until heated through.
Add cheese.
Heat until melted.

title: chessy squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taco soup
directions: Saute onion and peppers together; mix with browned hamburger. Add beans, corn, tomatoes, salsa and taco mix.
Simmer.
If too thick, add chicken or beef broth.

title: cheese-sausage souffle
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Wash in water and drain to remove excess grease.
Beat well with whisk all of the eggs.
Add milk and mustard; beat again.
Add cubed bread and sausage; mix well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pear preserves cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together, adding eggs, one at a time.
Mix soda, flour, allspice, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add buttermilk and flour mixture alternately to butter mixture.
Add vanilla, pear preserves and pecans.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan in 300° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Can substitute apricot preserves for pear preserves. Yield:
12 servings.

title: hamburger green bean casserole
directions: Cook and drain the hamburger, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Add green beans, thickened with tomato juice.
Prepare and mash potatoes (amount for family).
Line dish with potatoes. Add to it the hamburger and green beans and
tomato sauce mixture. Top with cheese.
Warm in oven.

title: italian steak
directions: Brown steak, cut into 2 or 3-inch squares. Add can of stewed tomatoes, basil and oregano, adding broth or water last. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Thicken slightly before serving.

title: mushroom swiss steak
directions: Cut steak in serving pieces.
Brown in 2 tablespoons of oil on both sides.
Place in casserole dish.
Put a slice of onion on each piece.
Spoon soup (undiluted) over meat.
Cook in a 350° oven, covered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour until tender.
Enjoy!

title: beef burgundy
directions: Heat fat in heavy pot and brown meat.
Remove, saute onions and mushrooms in butter until limp.
Return meat and add water, wine, bouillon cubes, garlic, salt and herbs.
Bring to boiling point, reduce heat, cover and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions and celery.
Cook another hour.
Thicken gravy if desired.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together and spread into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350° and let cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients well and spread over pretzel crust.
Dissolve Jell-O into boiling water.
Add thawed cartons of strawberries, can of crushed pineapple and mashed bananas.
Mix well and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill and cut to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together (not crumbs and margarine). Take 4 or 5 slices of bread (about 2 cups), toast to let bread get hard, not brown.
Melt 1 stick margarine and add to bread crumbs. Mix.
Put chicken mixture in an 8 x 11-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crunch Mix:
Put oats, flour and brown sugar in bowl; cut in margarine.
Place half of this mixture in bottom of pan.

title: dinah's cheesecake
directions: Mix all crust ingredients together.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of mixture for topping.
Press remainder into bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: texas cake(brownie cake)
directions: Combine cake flour, sugar, salt, eggs, sour cream and soda. Bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil.
Add cocoa mixture at once to flour mixture.
Mix well and pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix with Bisquick and sausage.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: honey orange chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut tips off wings; reserve for another use.
Halve remaining wings at joint.
Blend remaining ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken wings; turn to coat.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes.
Baste occasionally until chicken is tender and sauce is thickened.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Combine all and serve with crackers or party breads.

title: rice meat loaf
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Form into loaf and place in baking pan.
Spread surface with mustard and top with remaining sauce.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: my buttermilk brownies
directions: In a saucepan combine butter, cocoa and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, soda and salt; stir in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add cocoa mixture, mixing until blended. Pour into a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Immediately pour Cocoa-Buttermilk Frosting over brownies.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: dip for vegetables or chips
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: grape-nut cookies
directions: Pour cereal in bowl.
Add peanut butter.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes according to desired crunch.
Let it set for a while. Then eat!
Yum! Yum!

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: "Put macaroni in 65 ounces of water in pot.
Cook for 61 minutes.
Put cheese in with macaroni.
Stir it all up.
Put lid on pot.
Wait 25 minutes, take lid off and stir and eat it."

title: 1 bowl chocolate cake
directions: Mix up all dry ingredients in a large bowl, then add buttermilk, oil and eggs. Add water and stir good. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Mix all together (except pineapple and carrots) for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add pineapple and carrots and mix well.
Pour into three 8 or 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix squash and onions with other ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Turn 2 or 3 times.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bring butter and water to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in flour until well mixed and forms a ball.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Press down to form dessert shell.
Cool.

title: party mix
directions: Mix cereal, pretzels and pecans in baking dish.
Melt butter and add salt, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over cereal mixture and cook for 2 hours in a 225° oven.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: georgia peaches and cream cake
directions: Mix together.
Makes 4 layers.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except dressing.
Place half of dressing in bottom of casserole dish.
Add ingredients on top.
Dab with butter.
Cook at 375° until bubbly, then put rest of dressing on top for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: maryland crab meat
directions: Pick over crab meat for shells.
Sprinkle Wye River or Old Bay seasoning over crab meat.
Beat egg; mix in mayo, mustard, Worcestershire, lemon juice, crumbs and crab meat.
Mix; make patties.
Fry in butter until brown on both sides.
Serve.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry rice salad
directions: Cook the rice in the water, salted, for 20 to 30 minutes. Drain and save water (1/2 cup).
Dissolve the jello in the reserved 1/2 cup water. Combine jello, sugar, warm rice and pineapple. When cooled, add Cool Whip. Stir and chill.

title: thick crust pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast with 1 cup of warm water.
Add sugar, salt, oil and flour; let sit for 15 minutes.
Grease pan and fingers; spread dough flat.
Add sauce, cheese and toppings as desired.

title: winter chicken bake
directions: Wash potatoes.
Cook, covered, in a large saucepan in boiling water for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Peel and mash potatoes (should have 3 cups).
Stir in half the cheese and half the onions.
Spread potato mixture over bottom and up sides of a greased 2-quart rectangular baking dish or casserole to form a shell.

title: drunk dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into 4 to 5 pieces.
Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Melt over low heat and boil sauce until slightly thick. Serve hot in chafing dish with cocktail picks.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens (about 10 minutes).
Remove from heat, add 1 cup coconut and 2/3 cup chopped pecans.
Beat until cool and thick (by hand).
Excellent on most any flavor cake.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Day 1:
The day you receive starter, do nothing.
This is the starter:
1 cup sugar, 1 cup plain flour and 1 cup milk; stir with a wooden spoon.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Toss lightly. Pile lightly into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and cinnamon.
Blend in melted margarine.
Press over bottom of lightly greased spring-form pan.
Chill.
Blend cream cheese, sugar, flour and grated orange rind.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and egg yolks, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Stir in milk and pour into crumb crust.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes. Lower heat to 200° and bake 1 hour longer.
Turn off oven and let cake remain in oven until cool, about 1 hour.
Top with Fruit Glaze of your choice.
Makes 16 servings.

title: escalloped corn and cheese
directions: Pour egg into 6-cup buttered casserole.
Heat corn and milk and gradually stir into beaten egg.
Add salt, bread crumbs and cheese and mix thoroughly.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach 'n cream cheese
directions: Cook spinach as directed; drain well.
Combine spinach with softened cream cheese.
Mix well.
Season with salt and pepper. Cover with bread crumbs; dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until bubbly hot.

title: cheese crowned meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine egg, water, salad dressing, seasoned salt and cereal.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir to break up cereal. Add ground beef and celery.
Mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add cheese for last 5 minutes.
(Cut slices in half diagonally and arrange as triangles across top.)
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with soda.
Combine butter, sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts (batter will be stiff).
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onion until onion is tender.
Drain clams. Add clam liquor, potatoes and water to onion and bacon; cook about 10 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Add clams; heat through. Just before serving, add milk; heat to simmer.
Serves 4.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients together in measuring cup in order given.
Mix first 3 ingredients together in large bowl.
Add vegetable shortening.
Must not be lard or liquid shortening or animal fat.
Use Crisco, Spry or store brand vegetable shortening. Cut shortening in with dry ingredients until sizes of pieces vary from "pea size" to crumbs.
Add liquid ingredients and mix until blended.
Then use your hands to combine crumbs from bottom of bowl with rest of dough.
Divide into six parts for large 9-inch pies or seven parts for 8-inch pies.
Roll out on floured surface, turning over at least once. Mixture may be soft and absorb additional flour.
Fit into pans and trim edges.
All cut-off dough pieces may be remixed into remaining dough.
Be rough with this dough.
Handle it as much as necessary.
It keeps about 2 weeks wrapped in waxed paper in refrigerator or frozen for 3 or 4 months.

title: quick quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease loaf pan.
Make bottom layer with bread and cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and pepper.
Use half egg mixture to cover bottom layer.
Repeat bread and cheese layer, then pour remaining egg mixture over top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: kugel(noodle pudding)
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.

In large bowl, combine noodles, eggs, sugar (except 5 tablespoons), margarine (except 5 tablespoons), sour cream, cream cheese and lemon juice. Place in baking dish and refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour and butter together as for pie crust.
Beat eggs and add sugar.
Beat until thick.
Add soda, baking powder and vanilla to egg mixture.
Combine by adding flour-butter mixture to beaten egg combination.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet and press down with glass.
Or these make wonderful cut out cookies.
Chill batter.
Roll about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350°
for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: uncle jack's cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and blend in flour.
Add milk and other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thick, approximately 7 minutes.
Serve over cooked and drained broccoli or asparagus.
Can be used in other dishes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Drain hamburger meat; mix all ingredients together.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: the best play dough recipe(cleans your pans, too!)
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture gathers on stirring spoon and forms dough. This will take about 6 minutes.
Dump onto waxed paper until cool enough to handle and knead until smooth.
Store in covered container or plastic bag.
Food coloring may be added. (After cleaning, your stainless steel pans will shine because of the cream of tartar!) Makes about 2 pounds of play dough.

title: coconut-upside down cake
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Do not over heat.
Sprinkle brown sugar over margarine; arrange pineapple slices over sugar mixture. Fill center with cherry and fill between circles with pecans. Sprinkle with coconut all over.
Pour cake batter over all.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Slice onions and tomatoes.
Put in a large pan.
Put 2/3 cup table salt on top and set for 3 hours; drain.
Combine sugar and vinegar and bring to a boil; drop mixture into it.
Add mustard and turmeric.
Cook until tender.
Add cornstarch which has been mixed with 1/2 cup of cold water.
Stir into mixture.
Cook until thick. Be sure to stir as it will stick after adding cornstarch.
Put in sterile jars.

title: doughnuts
directions: Soften butter with a fork, add sugar and well beaten eggs.
Mix 3 cups of flour with the other dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and mix to the first mixture.
If necessary, add more flour until the dough is soft.
Form a ball and refrigerate 1/2 to one hour to firm.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on a slightly floured board or table.
Cut with a pastry cutter in the shape of a doughnut.

When all the doughnuts are shaped and cut, cook in a deep fryer or a large skillet in which three inches of fat or shortening or vegetable oil has been heated to 325° approximately. Place 3 to 4 (depending on the size of the doughnuts and the surface of the frying pot available) gently into the heated fat/oil.
Cook one side until gold color shows on the edge, turn, cook the other side until golden; remove from pot and continue to cook rest of doughnuts.
Makes approximately 50 doughnuts.

title: stuffed potatoes(baked)
directions: Bake the potatoes.
Cut in half and scoop out meat.
Crumble. Now add remaining ingredients.
Toss together and refill potato shells.
Return to oven to brown.

title: dutch pigs in a blanket
directions: Mix and add enough milk to hold dough together.

title: meatzza
directions: Mix together meat, spices and half can of pizza sauce.
Pat mixture evenly over entire bottom of 10-inch skillet.
Pour remaining half can of pizza sauce over center of meat and spread to 1-inch from edge.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes. Continue cooking, uncovered, another 20 minutes.
Drain off fat. Arrange Mozzarella over meat; cover and let stand 3 to 4 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cornish game hens with rice stuffing(for two)
directions: Season hens inside and out with salt and pepper.
In a small saucepan, cook almonds, onion and rice in margarine for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add water, bouillon cube, lemon juice and salt.
Bring mixture to boiling, stirring to dissolve cube.
Reduce heat; cover and cook slowly about 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is fluffy.
Stir in drained mushrooms.

title: green chilies
directions: Mix together.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch brownie pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut and serve on crackers.

title: mom's bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers, slice thin and add onions and peppers.
Layer this with salt and ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Add ice as needed. Drain well.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices.
Let come to a boil and add cucumbers.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Seal in jars.
Makes 7 pints.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper. Gently stir in the beans.
Spoon half of the mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of the onions.
Spoon remaining bean mixture over the top.

title: mexican hash
directions: Saute chopped onions in a large skillet for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beef, chili powder, salt and pepper; cook 1 minute.
Add kidney beans and mix well.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes, turning occasionally to blend in any crisp crust.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, pepper, salt, onion, celery and eggs well.
Clean peppers well.
Stuff beef mixture in peppers.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
