Pour tomatoes over top; bake for another 45 minutes.

title: no-cook jams
directions: Mash berries through a sieve or strainer or put in blender. Combine berries and sugar.
Let this stand 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir powdered pectin into water and bring to boil. Boil rapidly 1 minute, stirring all the time.
Remove from stove. Add berries and sugar, which have been stirred together, to the pectin and stir about 2 minutes.
`If liquid pectin is used instead of powdered, no cooking is necessary.
Just add the berries and sugar which have been stirred together to 1/2 cup pectin and stir about 2 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine and mix well.
Cook in a deep fat fryer or electric skillet at 350° for 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or cinnamon.

title: crunch top potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in jelly roll pan.
Add single layer of sliced potatoes.
Turn over to butter both sides.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: easy chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, salt, soda, and brown sugar together.
Add in shortening. Beat in egg and milk. Drop on ungreased sheet. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Frost with chocolate icing when hot and it is like a glaze when they cool, if you like.

title: low carb pizza crust
directions: Beat together cream cheese and eggs until smooth. Add cream cheese, Parmesan cheese and spices and mix together again. Spray a 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Sprinkle 2 cups of Italian cheese onto pan and pour the egg mixture over the cheese. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand for 5 minutes; add pizza sauce and favorite pizza toppings.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Spread on top of crumbs mixture.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Top with 8 ounce Cool Whip.
Sprinkle frozen Heath bars on top.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Layer crackers in a large bowl.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk and Cool Whip (fold in).
Layer all pudding with crackers, ending with crackers on top.
Melt chocolate icing in microwave until spreadable.
Spread on top of crackers and chill.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar, water, eggs, salt and vanilla together until smooth.
Then, gradually add flour, a little at a time, until all flour is used up.
Mix together.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Space them apart enough so they won't spread together. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes or until done.

title: jessica's baby pizzas
directions: Mash canned biscuits flat on cookie sheet.
Spread spaghetti sauce over each biscuit.
Top with variety of toppings from list. Use any or all.
Put in oven and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: easy nachos
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish. Pour beans over cream cheese.
Pour salsa over beans.
Top with shredded cheese.
Heat in microwave until hot and cheese is melted, approximately 10 minutes.
Serve with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: greek spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in lightly salted water until done; reserve stock.
Skin chicken; cut into small pieces.
Saute pepper and onions in butter.
Add olives, mushrooms, tomatoes, Greek seasoning to taste and reserved chicken stock.
Simmer 15 minutes. Add chicken pieces; simmer 5 more minutes.
Cook pasta in salt water; drain.
Layer half pasta, half sauce and half cheese; repeat.
Top with cheese.
Place in oven at 325° until cheese is melted.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute pecans in butter and cool before starting ice cream. Add sugar gradually to beaten eggs.
Beat until stiff.
Add other ingredients.
Freeze partially, then add pecans.
Continue freezing.

title: apricot upside-down skillet cake
directions: Using heavy-bottom skillet which has a tight-fitting lid, on medium low heat (or use an electric skillet set at 250°), melt butter.
Then stir in honey and simmer until well mixed and beginning to thicken.
Arrange apricots over the mixture, with cut side down.
Cover with nuts.
Cream butter and honey together, then add eggs one at a time, beating until smooth.
Add vanilla. Combine buttermilk or yogurt with soda.
Add flour and mix well. Pour batter over the apricots, spreading evenly.
Cover with lid (with vent open) and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove immediately by inverting a large cake plate over pan and turning upside down.
Serve warm or cold, topped with sour cream, if desired.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: Crush wafers and combine with butter.
Generously grease spring-form pan with butter.
Press crumb mixture (cookies and butter) on bottom of pan.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler. Remove from heat.
Gradually add slightly beaten egg yolks, vanilla and Amaretto.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Beat cream.
Fold cream into chocolate mixture.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 5 hours before serving.

title: frosting
directions: Combine shortening and powdered sugar slowly with a small amount of milk, 2 tablespoons.
Mix well.
Continue to add remaining ingredients.
The key to smooth frosting is good powdered sugar (no lumps); mix a long time for smoother frosting.
Any flavor may be added to recipe (vanilla, almond, cherry, etc.). Choose only one for a different flavor; add only 1 teaspoon.
This will frost a 9x 13-inch cake.

title: portuguese beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven quickly cook meat, half at a time, in hot oil till browned.
Return all meat to pan.
Stir in the two cups of water, the tomato sauce, bay leaves, vinegar, salt, garlic powder, crushed red pepper, cinnamon, and allspice.
Simmer covered for 1 hour.

title: "texas hash"(beef stroganoff)
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain well.
Add soup to pan and brown.
Add sour cream and drained peas, simmer for 10 minutes. Serve over egg noodles, toast or rolls.

title: wheat salad
directions: Soak 1 1/2 cups wheat overnight and cook 2 hours.
Soften cream cheese.
Sprinkle pudding over cheese.
Stir in lemon juice, pineapple, wheat and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: trifle(a big hit at any party!)
directions: Combine chocolate chips, cream cheese and evaporated milk in medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in walnuts and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Blend well.
Set aside.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cream butter; add cocoa and sugar.
Alternate milk until you can spread, then add vanilla.
Makes 3 cups.
This makes a lot, you can half the recipe.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Cook sugar and syrup in medium pan, stirring constantly until a rolling boil.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour syrup over egg whites a little at a time.
Continue beating.
This recipe will cover an 8 or 9-inch cake.

title: chocolate marshmallow fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter; cook at medium-high heat for 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add chocolate chips, vanilla and marshmallow cream.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased pan, cut into squares when cooled.

title: cream puff and eclair shells
directions: Melt butter in water in saucepan and bring to a boil and then lower heat.
Add salt and flour, all at once, stirring rapidly. Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture leaves side of pan and gathers around spoon.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Continue beating until smooth and glossy and break off when spoon is raised.

title: tortilla soup(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cut tortillas into chips.
Deep fry chips in oil, heated to 375°.
Add chips in batches and fry until golden brown.
Drain well.
Heat small amount of oil in large saucepan.
Add onions and saute until clear.
Add broth, tomato sauce, tomatoes, garlic powder and hot pepper sauce; simmer for 20 minutes.
Place a few chips in individual soup bowls.
Fill 3/4 full with soup and top generously with cheese.
Serve with remaining tortilla chips.

title: candied potatoes
directions: Boil and slice potatoes.
Layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sugar, syrup, juice and water.
Heat.
Pour over potatoes and sprinkle lightly with mace.
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°.
Baste as they cook.
(Freezes well.)

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together.
Roll into balls and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 50.

title: caramel icing
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil.
Brown 1/2 cup sugar in iron
skillet
and	pour
into mixture.
Cook to soft ball. Add vanilla.
Beat
with
mixer until light color and ready to spread. May use
as
fudge
by
adding
nuts and placing in a buttered dish.
I always use Duncan Hines Butter cake mix.

title: poor man's pate(braunschweiger mold)
directions: Have first 2 ingredients at room temperature.
Whip the first four ingredients together.
Soften gelatin in small amount of consomme.
Heat remaining consomme and dissolve gelatin in it. Pour a small amount (about 1 inch) of consomme into a 4 cup mold. Chill until set.
(Don't wait too long, or gelatin "top" may separate from other mixture when unmolded.)
Pour remaining consomme into Braunschweiger mixture and mix well.
Pour over set consomme in mold.
Chill until firm.
To serve, dip mold a few seconds in a bowl of hot water; turn over onto serving plate and serve with crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew the chicken and remove from the bones.
Place in casserole dish. Combine soups and sour cream. Spoon this mixture over the chicken. Crumble the crackers over casserole.
Melt 1/2 cup oleo and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cook asparagus or use canned.
Make a white sauce of oleo, flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook until thickened and add cheese.
Place half of bread crumbs in a greased casserole dish. Place alternate layers of eggs, asparagus and cheese sauce on top of the crumbs.
Cover top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet, add steak cubes and brown all over.
Add salt, pepper, tomato soup and half of the beef consomme.
Stir to make a smooth sauce.
Add onion and mushrooms. Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant and potatoes; use same amount of potatoes as eggplant.
Boil until tender.
Drain and mash. Add butter and milk, enough to make casserole of spreading consistency.
Add onion.
Put in baking dish with cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter with cinnamon and sugar.
Pat graham cracker crust into a large pie tin.
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream and place on crust.
Refrigerate several hours.
Top with pie filling.

title: poor man's stew
directions: In a pot (I use my crock-pot for this but you can cook on stove if you wish), mix broth, 2 cups water and vegetables that have been cut up.
Vegetable amounts depend upon the amount of broth that you have; these amounts are approximate.
Cook slowly until vegetables are tender.
Keep hot.

title: taste like more pretzel
directions: Place pretzels aside.
Combine butter and garlic powder. Microwave on High 35 to 40 seconds.
Stir.
Drizzle mix over pretzels.
Sprinkle with cheese and mix.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes until toasted.

title: bisquick bars
directions: Combine Bisquick and brown sugar.
Add eggs and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool before cutting into bars.

title: baked french breakfast doughnuts
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar; add egg and mix well. Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Fill greased muffin tins half full. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Melt butter. Mix together 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. When muffins are done, remove from tins and roll in melted butter, then in sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Yield: 8
muffins.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients. To serve, mix 2 tablespoons mix with 1 cup hot water.

title: cinnamon french toast(low-fat)
directions: Whisk egg and whites until foamy.
Add milk, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat well; set aside.
Spray a large non-stick skillet with cooking spray.
Dip 4 bread slices into egg, turning to coat.
Cook until golden, about 1 to 2 minutes per side.
Serve warm with cinnamon sugar or maple syrup.

title: sue's graham cracker cookies
directions: Line jelly roll pan with graham crackers. Melt butter. Add brown sugar and boil only 2 minutes. Pour over graham crackers. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle on chocolate chips immediately.

title: teriyaki wings
directions: Make marinade.
In medium bowl, combine salad oil with all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken in 9 x 14-inch baking dish; pour marinade over pieces. Cover at least 6 hours, turning occasionally.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange wings on wire rack in shallow roasting pan.
Bake 40 minutes, basting until tender, turning once.
Makes 3 dozen pieces.

title: pasta supper salad
directions: Combine water and garlic salt.
Bring to boil.
Gradually add pasta.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Place in bowl. Stir in lemon juice and oil; chill at least 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill well.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Can add cubes of meat or cheese or both.

title: chelsea buns
directions: Combine potatoes, water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Sprinkle yeast on top.
Let stand until bubbly.
Add the rest, stirring in enough flour to make a soft dough (not as stiff as bread dough).
Knead until smooth.
Let rise until double in bulk.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients until dough sticks together.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake about 25 minutes. Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.
Can freeze and reheat.
Makes about 75.

title: funeral pie
directions: Mix cream, raisins, brown sugar, salt, beaten eggs and cornstarch and mix smoothly with lemon juice and spices.
Beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 375° oven until firm.

title: butter roll
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
This will make a stiff dough.
When it's stiff, pinch off a small amount and roll real thin.
Sprinkle about 2 tablespoons sugar down the middle.
On top of sugar add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Then slide 1/4 of a stick of butter on top of the sugar and vanilla.
Fold in the dough around vanilla, sugar and butter to make a roll.
Layer sheet cake pan with butter rolls.
Sprinkle rolls with sugar.
Then completely cover with sweet milk.
Bake at 400° for about 20 to 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: powdered sugar cookie
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add powdered sugar and cream mixture.
Add egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat. Sift and add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix.
Stir in nuts.
Drop on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
While still hot, roll cookies in powdered sugar.

title: hot dog salad
directions: Slice and fry hot dogs.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Drain corn. Mix all together.
May be served hot or cold.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Let rise
(next
to
or over someplace warm).
Roll out dough to	1/2-inch
thick.
Cut out rolls and place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise again before baking.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt Velveeta, stirring constantly (be careful not to scorch!).
Add mayonnaise and potatoes to melted cheese and mix well.
Place into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and top with crumbled bacon.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
If baked directly from freezer*, increase baking time to 1 hour.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, melt chips and margarine. Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press 1/2 mixture firmly onto bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: fruit cookies(betty)
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 275°.

title: caramel cake(burnt sugar)
directions: *To Make Caramelized Sugar:
Place 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 cup hot water in skillet over medium heat; stir constantly until melted and quite dark.
Remove from fire.
Add 1/4 cup hot water; stir until dissolved.
Cool.

title: water chestnut casserole
directions: Boil celery in salty water for 7 minutes.
Drain and slice water chestnuts.
Mix with celery and chicken soup.
Put in a casserole dish.
Saute package of crushed crackers and sliced almonds in the butter.
Put on top of soup mixture in casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: denver omelette
directions: Scramble eggs with milk until fluffy.
Set eggs aside.
Brown ground beef.
Drain excess grease off.
Set aside.
Chop peppers, onions, ham and cheese.
Set aside.
Take eggs and pour into hot, greased frying pan.
Take ground beef, peppers, onions, ham and cheese, in that order.
Place only on one side of eggs.
Fold other half of eggs over, completely covering ingredients.
Turn only one time.
Serve with Tabasco sauce on top.
Makes 1 serving.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Pour pudding over pineapple.
Spoon carton of Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle fine chopped nuts over cake for decoration.

title: grapenut custard
directions: Put all ingredients, except Grapenuts in blender.
Blend thoroughly.
Add 1/2 of the Grapenuts and blend only a little.
Add enough milk to fill blender.
Pour in loaf pan or round baking dish.
Pour rest of grapenuts on top.
Bake at 350 till set, about 45 minutes.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Grease and flour 9-inch square cake pan.
Boil raisins with soda and water until 1/2 cup water remains.
Then add 1/2 cup water.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add Crisco and sugar and blend.
Add raisins and water.
Blend.
Flour gumdrops and nuts and add to mixture.
Stir well.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: quick little pizzas
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain off fat.
Flatten each biscuit with hand.
Put about 1 tablespoon pizza sauce on each biscuit. Next, add hamburger meat.
Top with Mozzarella cheese or other desired toppings.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes, until biscuits are brown around edge.

title: chili lasagna rolls
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Spread one side of each noodle with 3 tablespoons of chili; top with 2 pieces of cheese.
Roll up, placing seam side down, in a greased loaf pan.
Spread remaining chili atop rolls.
Bake covered with foil at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot.

title: pineapple coconut chess pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla, stirring until blended.
Stir in oleo, coconut and pineapple; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set, covering with aluminum foil after 40 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In large mixing bowl, cream margarine, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add flour, potato chips and chopped nuts. Mix well. Form into 1 1/2-inch balls and place 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Grease bottom of a glass about 3-inches in diameter. Dip greased glass into sugar and use to flatten each ball. Place nut half in center of each cookie. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheets. Then cool on wire racks. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: all-purpose refrigerator dough
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add shortening and work dough with fingers or pastry blender as for pie crust.
Add yeast, mixed with 1/2 cup lukewarm water and thoroughly dissolved, according to directions.
Add buttermilk and knead with hands only until all ingredients are thoroughly mixed.

title: easy rice and mushrooms
directions: Combine rice, consomm,
French onion soup and mushrooms in 13 x 9 baking dish. Arrange butter over rice mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Salt and pepper chicken; brown in butter.
Put rice in a 3 to 4-quart covered casserole dish.
Stir in salt and basil.
Pour broth over rice.
Lay chicken on top. Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour, or until all liquid is absorbed. Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: country-style potatoes
directions: Saute onion in shortening until tender; combine with corn, parsley and potatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Heat, stirring occasionally.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook the water, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Add the strawberry jello.
Cool mixture and pour over berries. Refrigerate until sets about 1 hour.

title: barbara's strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries. Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 mixture into 1 1/2-quart dish. Chill until set, then spread sour cream evenly over set Jell-O. Add rest of mixture.
Chill until set.

title: deep chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients only using 3 tablespoons of cocoa. Add milk and butter.
Beat until well blended.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Spoon into greased 2-quart baking dish.

title: beef casserole
directions: Mix the whole mess together.
Bake, uncovered, 3 hours at 325°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Prepare pastry shells according to package directions.

title: my hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Use 1/3 to 1/2 cup to 1 cup hot water.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: pecan pralines candy
directions: Boil the sugar, molasses, cream and butter until when a drop of cold water forms a soft ball.
Stir in the vanilla.
Pour mixture over the nuts and stir until it begins to sugar.
Drop from tip of spoon in small piles on buttered pans.

title: party size white castle hamburgers(appetizer)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except buns.
Cut buns in half.
Spread mix on buns and cover with foil.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: vanilla glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat until smooth.

title: pork casserole
directions: In hot oil in large skillet, brown pork strips well. Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Saute until tender.
Mix in all the seasonings. Simmer, covered, 25 minutes. Blend in soup, milk and cheese. Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rotoni in boiling water for 7 minutes.
Drain rotoni. Add onion flakes and cucumbers.

title: low-fat cheese cake
directions: You will need a 9-inch pan.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Melt squares of chocolate and butter together; cool slightly and add eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and pinch of salt.
Beat until smooth and pour into buttered pan (pie).
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Serve hot with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: busy day cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a small mixing bowl combine all ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Turn into pan.
Bake in 375° oven 25 to 30 minutes or till done.
Cool.
Serves 9.

title: meatballs in gravy
directions: Mix first six ingredients together. Shape into balls.
Brown in a small amount of margarine.
Pour mushroom soup and milk over meatballs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook Stove Top stuffing according to recipe on box.
Cook chicken and cut up in bite size pieces.
Mix 3 soups.
Layer half of the stuffing in casserole dish.
Place cut up cooked chicken on top.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Layer with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes until hot.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Stew and debone chicken.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Break chicken breasts into chunks and layer over melted margarine.
Mix together cream of mushroom soup, onion and broth. Pour over chicken.
Top with peas and carrots.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash and beat potatoes until smooth.
Beat in eggs, add 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup margarine, salt and cinnamon.
Starting with 1/4 cup of orange juice, beat in just enough to make mixture moist and fluffy.
Spoon mixture into casserole (2 to 3-quart size).
Arrange pecans over top and sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar and drizzle with 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add milk and vanilla gradually. Melt oleo and add to mixture.
Pour peaches and juice into baking dish.
Dump batter into fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
May use other canned fruit.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine and let stand overnight. In morning, heat and drain.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: old fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Mix oil, molasses, egg and sugar.
Sift all dry ingredients into oil mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Chill dough at least 1 hour. Roll into balls (about 1 teaspoon), then roll each ball in white granulated sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for about 10 minutes.
Try not to overbake.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: congealed pear salad
directions: Place pears in a 9-inch square dish. Use a fork to crush the pears. Mix jello as directed on package. Use pear liquid and water. Pour over crushed pears. Stir in cheese and mayonnaise. Place in refrigerator to set. Cut into squares to serve.

title: fried soft shell crabs
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and baking powder.
Dredge crabs in flour mixture to coat well.
In a large frypan or electric skillet, heat about 1/2 inch of oil to 375°.
Add crabs and lower heat to 350°.
Cook crabs until browned, about 5 minutes on each side.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon pecan sticks
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and cinnamon.
Add egg yolk, reserving white.
Add 2 cups flour and a pinch of salt.
Mix well. Dough will be quite stiff.
Knead on waxed paper a few times, adding very little flour.
Mash out dough on a greased or sprayed 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Spread out unbeaten egg white over dough.
Hold pan upside down over sink and allow extra egg white to drip off.
Mash pecans into batter.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: "best ever" meatballs and gravy
directions: Combine ground beef and onion soup in a bowl, mixing well. Form into 1-inch meatballs.
Cook on medium heat until well browned.
Remove from pan, and drain.
Add mushroom soup to pan, with equal parts water; then brown.
Add meatballs.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: baked sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Use a 2-quart baking dish which has been greased.
Place layer of sweet potatoes and layer of sliced apples into baking dish.

title: green chile rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake approximately 30 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Top with cheese, if preferred.

title: egg white frosting
directions: Boil the sugar, water and corn syrup until they spin a thread (approximately 5 minutes).
Slowly add to the beaten egg whites. Add salt and vanilla.
Beat until thick and shiny.
I double this for an angel food cake.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix last 3 ingredients; pour over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Hope you like it!

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together; set aside.
Bring water, oleo, oil and cocoa to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over dry mixture.
Mix milk, eggs and vanilla together.
Add to batter. Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stouffer's apple walnut upside-down pie
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar; beat to combine.
Spread butter-sugar mixture in the bottom of a 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts over butter-sugar mixture.
Divide pie pastry in half; roll each half to 1/8-inch thick.
Carefully line prepared pie pan with dough so as not to make holes in dough with nuts. Trim even with edge of the pan.
Fill pan with cubed apples. Combine granulated sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; blend thoroughly; sprinkle evenly over apples.
Place top crust on pie and trim even withy edge of pan.
Prick top with tines of a fork. Seal crust edges and roll edges toward the center of pie.
There should be no crust touching the rim of the pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove from oven (sugar may bubble out). Carefully run a knife around the edge of pan to loosen pie; invert on a serving plate.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Remove pan.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: sweet ginger pickles
directions: Soak the cucumbers in brine for 10 days. Take out and cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Soak in alum water 24 hours (2 tablespoons alum to 1 gallon water). Dry off on cloth, then boil in ginger tea (2 heaping tablespoonfuls ginger to 1 gallon water) 1 hour.
Take out and boil in syrup (sugar, 1 teaspoon alum, vinegar and spices tied in thin cloth) for 3 to 5 minutes until clear.

title: maggie's chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in a shallow baking pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours in oven at 350°.

title: butch's chess cake
directions: Then mix with a mixer the sugar, eggs and cheese, then pour this mixture over cake and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs separately and then mix all the other ingredients together.
Bake in an 8 x 14-inch pan at 275° for an hour or until done.
Top with glaze.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together; refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Garnish with 4 hard-boiled eggs, sliced, just before serving.
Can be frozen before or after baking.
Makes 10 servings.

title: herbed peppers
directions: Combine peppers, onion, garlic, seasoning, salt and pepper flakes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: tortillas
directions: Mix together and add water, a little at a time, until dough is achieved.
Pinch off small amount of dough and roll out on floured board.
Fry just slightly on a greased griddle on both sides, if using for enchiladas.
Makes 12.

title: oreo cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and whipped cream together until smooth.
Then in separate bowl, mix eggs, flour and vanilla, then mix into cream cheese mixture.
Crush the Oreos and mix with the melted butter.
Press the Oreo mixture into a spring-form pan. Pour 1/2 the cream cheese mixture over the Oreo crust.
Crush the remaining Oreos and sprinkle over the cream cheese mixture.
Pour the remaining cream cheese mixture on top of the Oreo layer.
Cook at 300° for 80 minutes.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Add eggs and beat until thick and ivory color.
Add lemon juice, rind, butter and milk.
Beat just enough to blend.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° on rack just below the center until top is very brown and a knife inserted halfway between rim and center comes out clean, 50 to 60 minutes.
Good served warm.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken; cut into pieces.
Chop tomatoes.
Add tomatoes and onion to chicken.
Mix soup, sour cream and chilies in large bowl.
Tear tortillas into bite size pieces; set aside.
Combine cheeses.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer as follows:
Using 1/2 of each item:
chicken, tortillas, soup mix and cheese.
Repeat.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill several hours before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: no-knead french bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Scald milk and water.
Add shortening, salt and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast and 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar in 1/4 cup lukewarm water; add to first mixture.
Add 1/2 of flour and stir until smooth.
Add remaining flour; mix well. Cover and let rise until double (about 45 minutes).
Pour onto floured board; divide into 2 parts.
Roll as for pie crust, then roll up as for jelly roll.
Place both on a greased cookie sheet and cover.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: hattie coffer's sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine
sugar,
margarine, syrup and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in potatoes.	Pour mixture into a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Heat soup, sour cream, salt and pepper and pour over vegetables.
Top casserole with crushed cracker crumbs.
Drizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Thoroughly wash and dry strawberries.
Cut them in half. Place strawberries in cooked pie shell.
Mix water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook 2 to 5 minutes on low setting or until clear and thick.
Remove from heat and add strawberry gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over strawberries in crust.
Chill and top with whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternating with milk. Chill.

title: swedish walnut cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crispy garlic chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In medium bowl, combine garlic mushroom soup mix, mayonnaise and cheese; set aside. On baking sheet, arrange chicken. Evenly top chicken with soup mixture, then evenly sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Chill until firm in 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and chop broccoli into bite size pieces.
Add onion, bacon and cheese.
Mix mayonnaise, brown sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: spinach tortellini and porcini salad
directions: Place the dried mushrooms in a bowl and pour on boiling water to cover.
Let sit for 15 to 30 minutes, until the mushrooms are tender.
Drain through a cheesecloth or paper towel-lined strainer, reserving the liquid and rinse the mushrooms thoroughly in several changes of water, making sure all the grit is washed away.
Squeeze dry and chop coarsely.
Mix together the vinegar, garlic, olive oil, 2 tablespoons of the reserved mushroom soaking liquid and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook the tortellini and peas in boiling water.
Cook al dente; drain and toss with dressing, herbs and Parmesan cheese.
Line a salad bowl with the spinach leaves; top with the salad.
Serves 4.

title: sweet and spicy black bean salsa
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour dressing over bean mixture and toss to coat.
Cover and chill 1 hour or up to 1 day.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Excellent party dip.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn.
Mix all together and place in casserole dish. Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook beef, onions and celery together.
Drain, then add rest of ingredients together and cook for 1/2 hour.

title: reese balls
directions: Combine sugar, peanut butter and margarine.
Stir until sugar is blended.
Form into balls.
Melt chocolate pieces and paraffin in saucepan over double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on wax paper to cool.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Whip Eagle Brand until frothy.
Stir in lemonade; fold in container of Cool Whip and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: cheese onion roll-ups
directions: Combine first four ingredients and mix well.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up tightly.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: date nut roll candy
directions: Cook milk and sugar to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and dates.
Beat until dates dissolve or until moderately firm.
Add nuts and vanilla; beat until it begins to stiffen.
Pour on a wet cloth and roll into a stick.
Let cool, slice and eat.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt the stick of margarine and set aside to cool.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add the sugar, raisins, coconut, nuts, vinegar and vanilla.
Add the butter last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare rice; add other ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cheesy muffins
directions: Combine meal, flour and sugar in bowl.
Add grated cheese and blend.
Add milk, egg and shortening and stir until thoroughly blended.
Fill hot, greased muffin pans about 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 muffins.

title: "lib" slaw
directions: Grate cabbage (not fine).
Chop onion and cucumber.
Mix salt and pepper.
Pack into jars.
Add hot pepper.
Heat vinegar and water; pour over cabbage.
Refrigerate.
(Don't pack too tightly.)

title: orange candy slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well. Add 1 cup buttermilk.
Beat well.
Add soda to the other half cup buttermilk.
Add to mixture.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add orange slices, chopped.
Add dates, nuts and vanilla and blend.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake slowly 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: glazed pork chops(grilled)
directions: Season pork chops with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Place in shallow dish and mix all other ingredients thoroughly.
Pour over chops and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Heat the olive oil in a stockpot over medium-high heat.
Add the pancetta, garlic and onion.
Cook, stirring frequently, until lightly browned, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add the chicken broth and herbs.

Bring to a boil and stir in the tortellini. Simmer, uncovered, until the tortellini is cooked, 10 to 12 minutes. Stir in the crushed tomatoes and simmer another 5 minutes. Add the spinach and cook just until wilted, about 3 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Ladle the hot soup into bowls and top with a liberal sprinkling of grated Parmesan.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry quick bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of a 9 x 5-inch
or
x 4-inch loaf pan.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring
cup;
level
off.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar,
salt,
baking soda and cinnamon.
In blender container or food processor bowl with metal blade, combine strawberries, oil and eggs.
Cover; process until well blended.
Add to dry ingredients; stir until all dry particles are moistened.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick
comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan. Cool completely.
Wrap tightly and store in refrigerator.

title: frozen fruit bars
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Add all other ingredients. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, or cupcake holders. Freeze overnight.
Remove about 10 minutes before serving and cut into squares.

title: mexican chicken pie
directions: Take chicken off bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Combine enchilada sauce and soup, onion, garlic salt, pepper and chicken. In 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan, layer half the corn chips, chicken mixture and remaining chips.
Sprinkle cheese over chips.
Pour broth over mixture.
Bake at 350° until the cheese melts.

title: chocolate cherry delight cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of two 9-inch round pans with waxed paper.
In a large mixer bowl, combine sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Add milk, egg substitute, oil and vanilla. beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer; stir in boiling water (batter will be thin). Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans to wire racks.
Carefully remove waxed paper. Cool completely.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: In a double boiler, over simmering water, melt butter and blend in flour. Add enough hot water to make sauce thick.
Cook until smooth.
Add the yolks, lemon juice, salt, cayenne and onion salt.
Can be kept on double boiler for 30 minutes before it separates.
Reheat before serving.
If too thick, add more butter or hot water.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for first 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 more minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix soup (don't add water), mayonnaise, eggs, 1/3 cup of cheese, salt and pepper together. Mix into broccoli and pour into buttered baking dish.
Melt butter and cheese in saucepan and stir in stuffing crumbs.
Mixture will get lumpy.
Crumble stuffing mixture over top of broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Add to butter.
Split rolls.
Spread mixture inside rolls.
Cut ham and cheese size of rolls.
Add to rolls to create sandwich.

title: gene's quick gumbo
directions: Rinse chicken breasts thoroughly and cut into 1-inch pieces. Cut sausages in small slices.
Cook in water for about 5 minutes and drain.
In a large gumbo pan, dissolve mix in water.
Saute vegetables in 2 tablespoons of oil; add to boiling water.
Add chicken and sausages, Ro-Tel tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or corn bread. Grandchildren will love this.

title: almond paste cookies
directions: Add unbeaten egg whites to almond paste.
Beat with a mixer until smooth.
Add sugars gradually.
Add vanilla.
Work dough with hands or spoon until all are blended.
Drop by small teaspoon into sliced almonds, roll until coated.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet for 20 - 23 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: banana chocolate chip cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 the Cool Whip.
Spread over cool crust.
Mix pudding and milk until smooth and thick.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Spread remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with shaved Hershey bar. Refrigerate.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix well together and pour in milk.
Mix well.
Mold like a cake.
Keep wrapped in foil paper or sealed container. Refrigerate.

title: pan de sal(crispy dinner rolls from the philippines)
directions: Put the warm water in a small mixing bowl. Add yeast and 1 teaspoon of the sugar. Stir to dissolve. Let stand until creamy, about 10 minutes. In a large mixing bowl, combine remaining sugar and the oil and mix until smooth. Add salt, 1 cup of flour and the yeast mixture. Stir well. Add the remaining 5 cups of flour, 1/2 cup at a time, until the dough pulls away from the side of the bowl. Turn the dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth, supple and elastic, about 10 minutes. Lightly oil a large mixing bowl. Place the dough in it, turning once to coat all sides with oil. Cover with a damp cloth or plastic wrap and let sit in a warm place until the dough has doubled in volume, about 1 hour. Turn the dough onto a lightly floured surface and divide into 4 equal parts. Form each piece into a cylinder and roll out until the "log" is 1/2-inch in diameter. Using a sharp knife, cut each log into 1/2-inch pieces. Place the pieces flat side down onto 2 lightly greased baking sheets. Gently press down each piece to flatten.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix fruit cocktail with juice, eggs, flour and other ingredients.
Mix by hand and pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Mix together brown sugar, butter and chopped pecans. Sprinkle over uncooked cake and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onion and pepper.
Drain grease. Set aside.
Mix cornbread mix according to directions.
Add corn. Pour half into greased pan.
Add beef, then cheese.
Put rest of cornbread mix on top.
Bake at 375°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Bananas, kiwis, strawberries and blueberries may be used.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until creamy, then add flour and milk (alternate) together.
Add flavoring.
Last, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Put in greased and floured tube cake pan.
Put in cold oven.
I bake mine at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
It depends on your oven.
All ovens are a little different; try it at 325° and if too hot, try 300° and then try 350°.

title: sweet corn bread
directions: Cream together eggs, butter and sugar.
Thoroughly blend with other ingredients. Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Bake corn sticks 25 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: In a bowl, mix the Miracle Whip, vinegar, sugar and mustard. Add diced onion, chopped celery, diced eggs and potatoes.
Toss all together.
Finally, mix celery seed into all.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
